1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,650
-We have another occasion to celebrate.
-It really surprised me.

2
00:00:17,717 --> 00:00:19,886
It's about Hyun-suk.

3
00:00:19,953 --> 00:00:21,454
His grandson was born!

4
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:23,023
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK SEES HIS GRANDSON

5
00:00:23,089 --> 00:00:24,991
He's now officially a grandfather.

6
00:00:25,058 --> 00:00:26,626
Gramps!

7
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:28,361
-Gramps.
-She gave a safe birth.

8
00:00:28,428 --> 00:00:29,829
-Grandpapa.
-You're a grandpa.

9
00:00:29,896 --> 00:00:31,865
It hasn't hit me yet.

10
00:00:31,931 --> 00:00:35,735
How can someone who's as immature as me
have a grandson?

11
00:00:35,802 --> 00:00:37,103
It doesn't feel real.

12
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:39,973
Everyone kept saying he takes after me.

13
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:43,076
-Does this mean he gets free bus rides?
-Really?

14
00:00:43,143 --> 00:00:45,045
Do you now get to ride the bus for free?

15
00:00:45,111 --> 00:00:47,514
Having a grandchild isn't a requirement.
It's the age!

16
00:00:48,048 --> 00:00:49,416
FOR SENIOR CITIZENS OVER AGE 65

17
00:00:49,482 --> 00:00:52,285
-I thought it was for free all grandpas.
-I thought it'd be free.

18
00:00:52,352 --> 00:00:55,522
If anyone says anything
to hurt my grandson's feelings,

19
00:00:55,588 --> 00:00:57,223
-I will take you down!
-All right.

20
00:00:57,290 --> 00:00:58,825
-Okay.
-He's already so protective.

21
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:00,827
I'll keep an eye on you two, especially.

22
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,228
Okay. Fine.

23
00:01:02,295 --> 00:01:03,696
He loves his grandson so much.

24
00:01:03,763 --> 00:01:05,432
-He really does.
-He loves him.

25
00:01:05,498 --> 00:01:06,533
Again, congratulations.

26
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,769
CONGRATULATIONS, GRANDPA

27
00:01:09,836 --> 00:01:11,071
Hey, so anyway.

28
00:01:11,137 --> 00:01:14,174
-I'm seeing someone new here.
-You're correct!

29
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,109
We must introduce her.

30
00:01:16,176 --> 00:01:18,111
We're here with someone amazing.

31
00:01:18,178 --> 00:01:19,612
A chef who was deeply beloved

32
00:01:19,679 --> 00:01:21,881
by the viewers in <i>Culinary Class Wars 2.</i>

33
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:23,216
WITH 25 YEARS OF EXPERIENCE

34
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:24,851
<i>I'll make Chinese-style fritters.</i>

35
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,619
SHE CARRIED THE TEAM MISSION

36
00:01:26,686 --> 00:01:29,689
<i>A chef who came</i>
<i>with charisma and excellent skills.</i>

37
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,591
<i>The Queen and the Goddess</i>
<i>of Chinese Cuisine?</i>

38
00:01:31,658 --> 00:01:34,994
She came here today,
ready to take both of them down.

39
00:01:35,061 --> 00:01:38,231
Please welcome Witch With a Wok,
Chef Yi Moon-jung!

40
00:01:38,565 --> 00:01:39,699
WELCOME

41
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,035
Please look into the camera
and say hello to the viewers.

42
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:45,405
Hey, there.
The lady who does magic with her wok,

43
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:48,508
a chef who has only made
Chinese cuisine for the last 25 years,

44
00:01:48,575 --> 00:01:50,510
I'm Chef Yi Moon-jung.
It's great to meet you.

45
00:01:51,244 --> 00:01:52,512
WOW…

46
00:01:52,579 --> 00:01:54,114
She changed the vibe completely.

47
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:55,615
ALREADY FEELING HER CHARISMA

48
00:01:55,682 --> 00:01:58,518
I've been waiting desperately for so long.

49
00:01:58,585 --> 00:02:00,386
Now that I'm finally here,

50
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:02,122
it's time for me

51
00:02:02,188 --> 00:02:03,590
to work my magic.

52
00:02:04,224 --> 00:02:05,658
NOW THAT'S WITCH WITH A WOK!

53
00:02:05,725 --> 00:02:08,027
-She reminds me of a soldier too.
-Salute. She's like one.

54
00:02:08,094 --> 00:02:10,530
As you can tell by the tone of her voice,

55
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:13,133
She's a bit on "this" side.

56
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,801
HAHAHAHAHA…

57
00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:17,470
-Cray cray?
-Yes, she's a bit cray cray.

58
00:02:17,537 --> 00:02:20,373
-The Goddess is on that side too.
-Yes.

59
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:22,709
Eun-yeong seems so docile today.

60
00:02:22,775 --> 00:02:24,777
This seat feels extra chilly.

61
00:02:24,844 --> 00:02:26,913
What's Chef Moon-jung like?

62
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:31,184
-She's like a big sister in the industry.
-Big sis.

63
00:02:31,251 --> 00:02:33,453
I grew up watching her when I was younger,

64
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:37,557
and I always hoped to be just like her.

65
00:02:37,624 --> 00:02:39,826
-She got her tail between her legs.
-Of course.

66
00:02:40,126 --> 00:02:41,227
VERY POLITE

67
00:02:41,294 --> 00:02:42,562
Has she always been so meek?

68
00:02:42,629 --> 00:02:44,364
Honestly speaking, which one of the chefs

69
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,299
did you come here to take down?

70
00:02:46,366 --> 00:02:48,034
Sadly, the first one

71
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:50,136
-has to be Eun-yeong.
-Of course.

72
00:02:50,203 --> 00:02:51,905
-Me?
-Eun-yeong first.

73
00:02:51,971 --> 00:02:53,506
I heard her heart drop just now.

74
00:02:54,107 --> 00:02:56,176
HEART DROPS

75
00:02:56,242 --> 00:02:59,479
After that, I'll take down
all of you one after the other.

76
00:02:59,812 --> 00:03:01,481
A BRUTAL RESOLUTION

77
00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:02,949
She'll take us down one by one.

78
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:04,117
LOOK FORWARD TO IT…

79
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,386
WILL THE CHINESE CHEFS FIGHT EACH OTHER?

80
00:03:06,452 --> 00:03:09,455
It's now time to bring in
the fridge owners of the day.

81
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:13,660
We prepared special episodes
as we welcome the 2026 World Cup.

82
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:16,462
Chef Hyun-suk may have become a grandpa,

83
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:18,097
but these guests are the soccer dads,

84
00:03:18,164 --> 00:03:20,633
the two fathers of Korean soccer.

85
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,068
We had a bit of a delay,

86
00:03:22,135 --> 00:03:25,438
so they've been bickering
behind the screen in that while.

87
00:03:25,505 --> 00:03:28,741
Jung-hwan is taking forever.

88
00:03:28,808 --> 00:03:31,177
Stop worrying about him
and worry about yourself.

89
00:03:31,244 --> 00:03:32,745
This is your second time.

90
00:03:32,812 --> 00:03:35,548
-It's been eight years.
-Why do they keep having you back?

91
00:03:35,615 --> 00:03:37,784
I CAN'T STAND YOU

92
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:41,487
These two like to take jabs at each other.

93
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:44,190
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

94
00:03:44,257 --> 00:03:45,892
Come on out!

95
00:03:46,993 --> 00:03:49,128
-Do we get up?
-No.

96
00:03:49,195 --> 00:03:52,098
Please welcome the fridge owners
for the 2026 World Cup Special,

97
00:03:52,165 --> 00:03:55,702
soccer managers Park Hang-seo
and Choi Yong-soo! Welcome!

98
00:03:55,768 --> 00:03:58,605
It's great to see you two.
Please greet everyone.

99
00:03:58,671 --> 00:04:00,073
-Hello.
-Hello.

100
00:04:00,139 --> 00:04:02,075
-Please take your seat.
-Welcome.

101
00:04:02,141 --> 00:04:04,410
JOY TO THE WORLD
THE FATHER OF SOCCER IS HERE

102
00:04:04,978 --> 00:04:06,746
COURTEOUS…

103
00:04:06,813 --> 00:04:08,214
Hello, Manager Park.

104
00:04:09,349 --> 00:04:10,950
RUSHING OVER AT THE SPEED OF LIGHT

105
00:04:11,017 --> 00:04:12,051
Hello, sir.

106
00:04:12,118 --> 00:04:14,554
A 90-DEGREE BOW

107
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:16,990
-Now that we have former players here…
-He ran over.

108
00:04:17,056 --> 00:04:19,158
I'm going to have an exhausting day.

109
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,462
Jung-hwan seems so restless.

110
00:04:22,528 --> 00:04:25,398
-He's as restless as Eun-yeong is.
-I feel so uncomfortable.

111
00:04:25,465 --> 00:04:27,267
-It's killing me.
-He's in Eun-yeong's place.

112
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:29,969
He might be worse off, actually.

113
00:04:30,036 --> 00:04:31,337
Allow me to introduce him.

114
00:04:31,404 --> 00:04:33,539
<i>He then became a hero in Vietnam</i>
<i>with his Park Hang-seo magic.</i>

115
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:37,210
Please welcome Rice-dink,
soccer manager Park Hang-seo!

116
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,311
Thank you.

117
00:04:38,544 --> 00:04:39,879
MANAGER RICE-DINK

118
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:42,015
Allow me to introduce this man.

119
00:04:42,081 --> 00:04:44,450
He's simply a legendary striker.

120
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:45,652
HEHE

121
00:04:45,718 --> 00:04:47,287
-He was fantastic.
-He was.

122
00:04:47,353 --> 00:04:50,223
-I wasn't so bad.
-Choi Yong-soo!

123
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,258
-He went down in history.
-Of course.

124
00:04:52,325 --> 00:04:54,994
<i>The hero</i>
<i>of the miraculous World Cup semifinal run.</i>

125
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:57,230
<i>The first Korean soccer player</i>

126
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:02,669
<i>who won the K League as player, </i><i>coach,</i>
<i>and manager. He is the victory contractor!</i>

127
00:05:02,735 --> 00:05:04,971
The forever eagle, Manager Choi Yong-soo!

128
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:07,106
-Welcome to the show!
-Welcome!

129
00:05:07,173 --> 00:05:08,975
-The victory contractor!
-Yes

130
00:05:09,042 --> 00:05:12,011
-I was last here eight years ago.
-Eight years.

131
00:05:12,078 --> 00:05:13,413
BACK THEN, HE…

132
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:16,015
Everyone was nice except for you.

133
00:05:16,082 --> 00:05:18,751
Giving him a noogie on the head

134
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:20,186
wouldn't have been enough.

135
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:23,122
HITTING JUNG-HWAN WITH THE HARSH TRUTH

136
00:05:23,189 --> 00:05:25,858
Thank you so much for having me here.

137
00:05:25,925 --> 00:05:27,794
I'll have a great day eating good food.

138
00:05:28,061 --> 00:05:29,362
EXCITED FOR HIS REMARKS AND MUKBANG

139
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:30,830
STARING…

140
00:05:30,897 --> 00:05:33,099
Did you get eyebrow tattoos for today?

141
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,734
-I got makeup done.
-It's makeup.

142
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:36,002
PRETTY HANG-SEO

143
00:05:36,069 --> 00:05:38,838
So why are you calling me out
on my appearance?

144
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:41,874
It seemed like
you spruced yourself up today.

145
00:05:41,941 --> 00:05:45,211
Whether I spruced myself up or not,
that's none of your business.

146
00:05:45,611 --> 00:05:47,246
WHIMPER…

147
00:05:47,313 --> 00:05:48,848
Never…

148
00:05:48,915 --> 00:05:50,717
Stop pointing like that.

149
00:05:50,783 --> 00:05:52,485
DROPPING…

150
00:05:52,552 --> 00:05:55,254
-"Stop pointing like that."
-Do it like this.

151
00:05:55,321 --> 00:05:58,091
Never get caught up
in the way this guy talks.

152
00:05:58,157 --> 00:06:02,095
-We can't predict how things will go.
-This is going to be fun.

153
00:06:02,161 --> 00:06:05,465
So Manager Park, how have you been lately?

154
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:08,601
I've become the head of the support team
for the 2026 World Cup.

155
00:06:08,668 --> 00:06:10,236
-That's right.
-Yes.

156
00:06:10,303 --> 00:06:12,038
I live in Vietnam right now,

157
00:06:12,105 --> 00:06:15,541
so when I got the offer
to be on <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

158
00:06:15,608 --> 00:06:17,343
I suddenly had to come two days ago,

159
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:20,446
and I'm returning two days from today.

160
00:06:20,513 --> 00:06:22,348
-Thank you for having me.
-The thing is,

161
00:06:22,415 --> 00:06:26,319
Jung-hwan kept showing off,
saying we got you here, thanks to him.

162
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:27,820
That is completely groundless.

163
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:29,322
Is it now?

164
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:31,090
-It wasn't Jung-hwan?
-No.

165
00:06:31,157 --> 00:06:32,558
When we meet from time to time,

166
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:34,994
he keeps showing off by saying that

167
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:38,598
he knows all the chefs, so I can ask him
when I want to eat somewhere.

168
00:06:38,664 --> 00:06:42,735
-Me?
-He said I could ask him for a favor.

169
00:06:42,802 --> 00:06:45,605
-That only he can get you a spot?
-Only through him.

170
00:06:45,671 --> 00:06:47,373
What are you? A broker?

171
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:50,109
A STUMBLING BLOCK TO HIS DIRECT PASS

172
00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:51,944
To be honest…

173
00:06:52,011 --> 00:06:54,781
It killed my pride a little.

174
00:06:55,214 --> 00:06:56,682
DID HE REALLY ACT POMPOUS?

175
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:58,885
He reluctantly had to ask Jung-hwan
for a favor.

176
00:06:58,951 --> 00:07:00,553
He must've really wanted to go.

177
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:02,755
-When did I say that?
-Why would you…

178
00:07:03,022 --> 00:07:04,090
SO FUN TO WATCH
CACKLE…

179
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:06,392
What he said was this.
"Can I go to one of their restaurants?"

180
00:07:06,459 --> 00:07:08,628
-I said, "Reservations are tough."
-It is.

181
00:07:08,694 --> 00:07:11,564
Then he asked, "Can you ask?"
So I said, "I can't really do that."

182
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:13,733
-That was all.
-I see.

183
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,868
Are you going to stop seeing me
from now on?

184
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:18,771
-This is what he does!
-See?

185
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:21,107
Nothing has changed.

186
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:23,609
NEVER-CHANGING JUNG-HWAN
NOTE: SHOWS OFF A LOT

187
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:25,344
A STRIKER FIERCER THAN YONG-SOO

188
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:27,613
Manager Park is crazy.

189
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:31,217
Manager Choi has been coming here
for every World Cup special.

190
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,351
It's his second time.

191
00:07:32,418 --> 00:07:36,055
-Yes.
-It's not easy to be on the show twice.

192
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,857
I get that you called him twice,

193
00:07:37,924 --> 00:07:39,392
but is he worth the value?

194
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:41,327
WORTH THE VALUE

195
00:07:42,061 --> 00:07:43,496
A SUCKER PUNCH OUT OF THE BLUE

196
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:45,665
HANG-SEO ATTACKS EVERYONE

197
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:47,366
THIS IS EXCITING AND FUN

198
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:49,469
Jung-hwan said

199
00:07:49,535 --> 00:07:52,972
I would be on the show with Ji-sung.

200
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:56,809
So I thought, "I could handle those two,"

201
00:07:56,876 --> 00:07:58,077
and gladly accepted the offer.

202
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:00,279
-You thought it'd be Park Ji-sung?
-Wait.

203
00:08:00,346 --> 00:08:01,981
Does this mean I was subbed?

204
00:08:02,381 --> 00:08:04,283
A CONSPIRACY

205
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:06,052
I thought you were subbed.

206
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:07,720
EACH THOUGHT THE OTHER WAS SUBBED

207
00:08:07,787 --> 00:08:10,423
-Wild rumors are flying everywhere.
-What's going on here?

208
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,692
SO WHICH ONE WAS THE STARTING PLAYER?

209
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:14,026
At first,

210
00:08:14,093 --> 00:08:16,963
I thought I was invited here alone.

211
00:08:17,029 --> 00:08:20,366
-Did you think it was a solo episode?
-He thought it was just him.

212
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,635
THE SOLO STARTING PLAYER

213
00:08:22,702 --> 00:08:24,871
You're really good on shows.

214
00:08:25,238 --> 00:08:26,939
HE'S ALWAYS ONE STEP AHEAD OF YONG-SOO

215
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:28,508
Then I heard Yong-soo will be here.

216
00:08:28,574 --> 00:08:31,644
-I told my agent, "Let's think about it."
-"Let's think about it."

217
00:08:31,711 --> 00:08:34,213
LET ME THINK IF THIS LINEUP IS RIGHT…

218
00:08:34,914 --> 00:08:36,849
There's a bit of a problem right now.

219
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:38,050
Back in the green room,

220
00:08:38,117 --> 00:08:41,287
he said, "We need
to expose Jung-hwan for who he is!"

221
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:44,290
-Jung-hwan's true nature?
-You two had an agreement?

222
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:47,627
But the direction seems to have changed.

223
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:49,428
-Don't attack me.
-He's not the enemy.

224
00:08:49,495 --> 00:08:51,697
-Their agreement isn't playing out.
-Not right now.

225
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:54,634
-Let's wrap this up right here.
-Let's wrap it up.

226
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:57,169
It's Manager Choi's second time here.

227
00:08:57,236 --> 00:08:59,539
I heard you analyzed
the problem with <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

228
00:08:59,605 --> 00:09:00,907
-The problem?
-Is that so?

229
00:09:00,973 --> 00:09:02,742
I think he's been here for too long.

230
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:04,911
CLAPPING

231
00:09:04,977 --> 00:09:06,012
It's been too long!

232
00:09:06,078 --> 00:09:08,648
-He doesn't deserve this spot.
-It's not like

233
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:11,083
he leaves that big of an impact.

234
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:13,085
A PLAYER WHO DOESN'T LEAVE AN IMPACT

235
00:09:13,152 --> 00:09:15,021
Can I talk to the production crew?

236
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:16,489
HOPING FOR A QUICK CHANGE

237
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:18,424
-Why him?
-I see.

238
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:21,160
-And sub the host out?
-Subbing him out?

239
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,562
What do you think?

240
00:09:22,628 --> 00:09:26,632
They're both soccer managers, so they
know a good tactic when they see one.

241
00:09:26,699 --> 00:09:29,001
You can relax and talk. I'm here to--

242
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:30,670
Sit upright.

243
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:32,305
YESSIR…

244
00:09:32,371 --> 00:09:34,307
He doesn't like to see bad posture.

245
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:36,943
UNPREDICTABLE ATTACKS

246
00:09:37,009 --> 00:09:38,611
He was slouching for just a second!

247
00:09:38,678 --> 00:09:40,746
-Yong-soo sat upright.
-That's not it.

248
00:09:40,813 --> 00:09:42,281
It was just for a moment, geez.

249
00:09:42,348 --> 00:09:45,017
I didn't think JTBC

250
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:49,155
would use that guy
if he didn't have any sort of value.

251
00:09:49,221 --> 00:09:50,756
They use him because he's worthy.

252
00:09:50,990 --> 00:09:52,058
COME ON, MAN…

253
00:09:52,124 --> 00:09:54,026
It's not his problem to care about.

254
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:55,695
MIND YOUR OWN, YONG-SOO

255
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:57,663
I came here

256
00:09:57,730 --> 00:10:00,132
to recommend Hang-seo for that position.

257
00:10:00,199 --> 00:10:01,801
GUFFAW

258
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:04,503
-It was for Hang-seo's sake!
-Thinking of Manager Park.

259
00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:06,472
-Man.
-He didn't know your intention.

260
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:09,842
-He's also very good with his words.
-He really is.

261
00:10:09,909 --> 00:10:11,677
Thanks.

262
00:10:13,012 --> 00:10:14,680
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY SO EARLIER?

263
00:10:14,747 --> 00:10:17,717
I guess he isn't that aloof.

264
00:10:17,984 --> 00:10:19,218
HEHE…

265
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:24,023
-There's high tension between the three.
-I can feel it.

266
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:27,326
There's a high-voltage current flowing.
Ow, that stings!

267
00:10:27,393 --> 00:10:29,128
If anyone dozes off,
they'll go straight down.

268
00:10:29,495 --> 00:10:32,465
VIEWERS, STAY VIGILANT

269
00:10:32,531 --> 00:10:34,166
Manager Park Hang-seo

270
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,335
is now famous as Rice-dink.

271
00:10:36,402 --> 00:10:38,337
During the 2018 Asian Games,

272
00:10:38,404 --> 00:10:42,708
he led Vietnam to the semifinals
for the first time in history.

273
00:10:42,775 --> 00:10:46,278
Also, in the 2018 ASEAN Championship,

274
00:10:46,345 --> 00:10:49,582
Vietnam took victory
for the first time in ten years.

275
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:52,118
Following that, in the 2019 SEA Games,

276
00:10:52,184 --> 00:10:57,390
<i>he led Vietnam to its first victory</i>
<i>in </i><i>60 </i><i>years.</i>

277
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,025
THAT'S AMAZING

278
00:10:59,358 --> 00:11:01,627
VIETNAM'S NATIONAL HERO

279
00:11:01,694 --> 00:11:04,630
-He's a hero in Vietnam.
-I believe he received three medals too.

280
00:11:04,697 --> 00:11:06,499
-Right?
-Is that so?

281
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:10,369
<i>He was the first foreign national</i>
<i>to receive a medal.</i>

282
00:11:10,436 --> 00:11:11,904
NO WAY

283
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:14,774
-The first foreign national to be awarded.
-Also,

284
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:18,144
he gets to fly business class
with Vietnam Airlines free for life.

285
00:11:18,210 --> 00:11:19,311
-Really?
-For life.

286
00:11:19,578 --> 00:11:21,213
A NEVER-BEFORE-HEARD PERK

287
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:23,916
I thought that it was just for a year

288
00:11:23,983 --> 00:11:26,018
for me and my wife.

289
00:11:26,085 --> 00:11:27,753
-And your wife?
-Yes.

290
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:31,123
It's not for the entire world, though.
Just between Korea and Vietnam.

291
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,725
-But still.
-That's amazing.

292
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:34,960
-That's the perk. Yes.
-For life?

293
00:11:35,227 --> 00:11:36,295
JEALOUS

294
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,997
In Vietnam, he rarely dines

295
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:40,132
with ordinary people.

296
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:42,201
I called him and said, "Hello. It's me."

297
00:11:42,268 --> 00:11:45,237
He said, "I'll call you back.
I'm with the Minister of Justice."

298
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:49,942
-He only dines with ministers.
-With high government officials.

299
00:11:50,009 --> 00:11:51,610
Don't believe a word of that.

300
00:11:51,677 --> 00:11:52,945
-It's true.
-That's made up.

301
00:11:53,012 --> 00:11:56,482
I can totally believe his stories.

302
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:58,884
-Just because you two are friends…
-I also think

303
00:11:58,951 --> 00:12:00,853
he seems to have changed lately.

304
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,722
-What? How?
-In what way?

305
00:12:02,788 --> 00:12:05,157
Ever since he returned from Vietnam,

306
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:06,926
he seemed a bit, you know…

307
00:12:09,161 --> 00:12:11,330
He's playing a legendary manager.

308
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:12,398
Playing a legendary manager?

309
00:12:12,765 --> 00:12:13,833
CACKLE

310
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:16,035
-Playing a what?
-He is a legendary manager!

311
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:18,537
DROPPING, THEN FEELING CONSCIOUS

312
00:12:18,604 --> 00:12:20,306
By playing a legendary manager,

313
00:12:20,372 --> 00:12:23,509
-I meant that you truly are a legend.
-He is.

314
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:26,045
DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT…

315
00:12:26,112 --> 00:12:28,447
-He's still feeling odd.
-It's the "playing" part.

316
00:12:28,781 --> 00:12:31,350
ANXIOUS

317
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:33,452
I've heard

318
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:36,922
Yong-soo speak with Jung-hwan
from time to time.

319
00:12:36,989 --> 00:12:39,558
He'd say, "Hang-seo told me
to come visit him in Vietnam,

320
00:12:39,625 --> 00:12:40,726
but why would I?"

321
00:12:40,793 --> 00:12:42,795
"I got a pho place near my place too."

322
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:45,164
ALREADY LIVES NEAR A PHO PLACE

323
00:12:45,231 --> 00:12:48,067
He's like, "Why would I?
I got a joint nearby."

324
00:12:48,134 --> 00:12:51,637
But I never even asked him to visit.

325
00:12:51,704 --> 00:12:53,005
You didn't ask him to come.

326
00:12:53,072 --> 00:12:55,274
-I've visited a few times.
-You have, right?

327
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:56,675
The moment I arrive at the airport,

328
00:12:56,742 --> 00:12:59,612
<i>you can see his face all over the ads.</i>

329
00:12:59,678 --> 00:13:00,780
It was fascinating.

330
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:03,682
-I once had to go there with him.
-With Hang-seo?

331
00:13:03,749 --> 00:13:05,151
Before we landed, he said,

332
00:13:05,217 --> 00:13:07,286
"Don't do anything. Just follow my lead."

333
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:09,121
How cool of him.

334
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:10,689
I didn't know what he meant by that.

335
00:13:10,756 --> 00:13:13,159
Then an officer came
and did our immigration immediately.

336
00:13:13,225 --> 00:13:15,127
He pretty much has a free pass.

337
00:13:15,427 --> 00:13:17,630
BLUSHING HANG-SEO

338
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:18,898
He's really that big?

339
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:20,032
People go crazy over him.

340
00:13:20,499 --> 00:13:21,801
STILL DOESN'T BUY IT

341
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:24,837
Yong-soo looks surprised.
I guess he didn't know how popular he was.

342
00:13:24,904 --> 00:13:27,940
Wait a second. We need to remove
some questions for Yong-soo.

343
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:29,809
He's way too interesting.

344
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:31,377
WORTHY AS A SOLO GUEST

345
00:13:31,443 --> 00:13:32,945
I think he's here as a solo guest.

346
00:13:33,012 --> 00:13:34,480
I'm leaving soon, anyway.

347
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:36,916
ANNOUNCES HIS VOLUNTARY WALKOUT

348
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,185
We have a recording

349
00:13:39,251 --> 00:13:42,021
of the conversation these two had
back in the green room,

350
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:43,789
including what they said in private.

351
00:13:43,856 --> 00:13:45,524
We're now tapping our guests?

352
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:47,860
NERVOUS

353
00:13:47,927 --> 00:13:50,596
I'm sorry, but can you sub for me
just for this episode? As the host?

354
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:53,432
-Is this tough for you?
-I'm feeling uneasy.

355
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:55,134
First of all, Manager Park

356
00:13:55,201 --> 00:13:58,604
<i>is the type</i>
<i>who takes great care of his team.</i>

357
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:02,041
<i>Some have even started</i>
<i>to call him Papa Leadership.</i>

358
00:14:02,107 --> 00:14:03,108
However,

359
00:14:03,776 --> 00:14:06,478
-Manager Choi said something like this.
-What did he say now?

360
00:14:06,545 --> 00:14:09,181
-"Everything is staged."
-Staged?

361
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:16,388
"He never came anywhere near the players
when he coached in Korea."

362
00:14:16,455 --> 00:14:18,924
-I was there at that time.
-You were?

363
00:14:18,991 --> 00:14:20,626
"Everything is staged."

364
00:14:20,993 --> 00:14:22,094
EVEN THE WITNESS REMEMBERS

365
00:14:22,161 --> 00:14:24,129
-"Everything is staged."
-We have a witness.

366
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:27,967
We'll need an explanation for this.

367
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:30,569
I believe I did say that.

368
00:14:30,636 --> 00:14:33,772
-He's straight with it.
-He's honest.

369
00:14:33,839 --> 00:14:35,241
STARE

370
00:14:35,307 --> 00:14:37,343
But you know,

371
00:14:37,409 --> 00:14:40,546
he has always been very warm at heart.

372
00:14:40,613 --> 00:14:43,082
He always stands with the players…

373
00:14:43,148 --> 00:14:44,884
How am I supposed to patch this up?

374
00:14:45,284 --> 00:14:46,485
FAILED ATTEMPT

375
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,254
-Right.
-I can't do it.

376
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,789
Was your Papa Leadership staged?

377
00:14:50,856 --> 00:14:52,024
I don't think so.

378
00:14:52,091 --> 00:14:53,626
Hey, man.

379
00:14:54,593 --> 00:14:57,363
-I know what he's like.
-Hang-seo. Stop!

380
00:14:57,429 --> 00:14:59,164
-He's always been like this.
-Hey, hey.

381
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:00,766
-Hey, hey.
-Jung-hwan

382
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:04,103
also took part in the conversation.

383
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:06,505
TRYING TO DRAG HIM INTO THIS

384
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,540
-Because he was jealous.
-You know I never lie.

385
00:15:08,607 --> 00:15:12,411
-I'm starting to get a bit steamy.
-You are?

386
00:15:12,478 --> 00:15:14,013
-He's fuming.
-I can see it

387
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:16,682
-Yes, he's turning a bit red.
-He's getting steamy!

388
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,584
HANG-SEO, CALM DOWN

389
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:20,619
I'm not the type who can stage anything.

390
00:15:20,686 --> 00:15:22,755
-He's not like that.
-It's not in my personality.

391
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:25,824
Yong-soo is more than capable of that.
He's good at staging things.

392
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:28,727
THE MASTER OF STAGING

393
00:15:28,794 --> 00:15:31,096
He knew because he stages those things!

394
00:15:31,163 --> 00:15:32,765
The more you know, the more you notice.

395
00:15:32,831 --> 00:15:35,067
SCORING AN OWN GOAL

396
00:15:35,134 --> 00:15:36,769
The more you know, the more you notice?

397
00:15:36,835 --> 00:15:38,237
HE ONLY NOTICES STAGED MOMENTS

398
00:15:38,304 --> 00:15:39,605
Yes, that's why…

399
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:42,708
There's something I saw in the green room.

400
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:43,809
He was looking at…

401
00:15:44,376 --> 00:15:46,779
You're doing that again! Come on.

402
00:15:46,845 --> 00:15:49,982
He said, "Do you know how to use ChoiPT?"
I said, "I don't know what that is."

403
00:15:50,049 --> 00:15:51,317
-ChatGPT?
-You mean AI?

404
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:55,654
We'll have to give our opinion
on the food that we eat later, right?

405
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:58,524
He was asking ChatGPT
to come up with stuff.

406
00:15:58,590 --> 00:16:01,660
-To give his take on the food?
-Come on.

407
00:16:01,727 --> 00:16:03,095
He came ready.

408
00:16:03,162 --> 00:16:05,397
-He got everything prepared.
-Let's hear it later.

409
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:06,899
I'm looking forward to next week.

410
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,435
-He wouldn't be quiet if he came prepared.
-He told me…

411
00:16:09,735 --> 00:16:11,403
EMBARRASSED

412
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:12,871
He looked at his screen and said,

413
00:16:12,938 --> 00:16:15,641
"Why don't you pick one out?"

414
00:16:15,941 --> 00:16:18,844
BEING GENEROUS WITH HIS AI RESPONSES

415
00:16:18,911 --> 00:16:21,847
Hey. How can you say that…

416
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:25,851
He exposed him.

417
00:16:25,918 --> 00:16:29,421
I'm trying to compliment you
by mentioning that you came prepared.

418
00:16:31,357 --> 00:16:37,029
You should've mentioned that I prepared
different versions for red meat and fish.

419
00:16:37,096 --> 00:16:38,664
AMAZED

420
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:41,500
-I'm so grateful that he did that.
-He came…

421
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:43,802
-He came prepared.
-He wanted to give a good review.

422
00:16:44,069 --> 00:16:46,872
PLEASE LOOK FORWARD TO CHOIPT'S REVIEW

423
00:16:46,939 --> 00:16:49,775
We're about to look through
Manager Park's fridge now.

424
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:53,412
His main residence is in Vietnam,

425
00:16:53,479 --> 00:16:57,149
and we couldn't bring
everything he had there.

426
00:16:57,216 --> 00:16:59,385
So we prepared a special fridge for him

427
00:16:59,451 --> 00:17:03,822
filled with ingredients
he uses often in Vietnam,

428
00:17:03,889 --> 00:17:07,292
and Korean food ingredients
he usually enjoys.

429
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:10,162
<i>It's a collaboration</i>
<i>between Korea and Vietnam.</i>

430
00:17:10,229 --> 00:17:13,165
So let's take a look
at Manager Park's fridge.

431
00:17:13,932 --> 00:17:16,535
I'm looking forward to this.

432
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:20,572
-We present Manager Park's fridge!
-Fridge!

433
00:17:24,576 --> 00:17:26,779
PRESENTING HANG-SEO'S FRIDGE

434
00:17:27,379 --> 00:17:30,616
FULL OF KOREAN AND VIETNAMESE INGREDIENTS

435
00:17:30,682 --> 00:17:34,186
-Look at how many sauces he has.
-He has lots of sauces.

436
00:17:34,253 --> 00:17:37,056
Vietnamese spring roll sauce. What's this?

437
00:17:37,122 --> 00:17:40,192
-Vietnamese chili sauce?
-Chili sauce?

438
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:42,661
Do you have a favorite sauce?

439
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:44,063
My favorite sauce

440
00:17:44,129 --> 00:17:46,598
is something called nuoc mam.

441
00:17:46,665 --> 00:17:48,033
-Nuoc mam
-Nuoc mam.

442
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,969
Oh, this must be nuoc mam.

443
00:17:51,036 --> 00:17:53,072
It's made like Korean fish sauce, <i>aekjeot</i>,

444
00:17:53,138 --> 00:17:55,307
-but it's a bit stronger.
-He's like an expert.

445
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:56,508
It has a funky smell.

446
00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:58,243
It smells fishy,

447
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:01,413
so I like to add garlic and spicy chili.

448
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:04,616
It's very delicious with morning glory.

449
00:18:04,683 --> 00:18:06,552
-Morning glory.
-Yes.

450
00:18:06,618 --> 00:18:09,755
In that case,
what's your favorite Vietnamese dish?

451
00:18:09,822 --> 00:18:11,924
As you all probably know,

452
00:18:11,990 --> 00:18:14,293
-Vietnam is long.
-Yes, the country is long.

453
00:18:14,359 --> 00:18:16,728
Hanoi is in the north,

454
00:18:16,795 --> 00:18:18,897
-Da Nang is in the middle,
-The middle.

455
00:18:18,964 --> 00:18:21,266
and Ho Chi Minh is in the south.

456
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:25,037
So the thing with the food is…
I'm usually in Hanoi,

457
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:29,541
<i>so I often eat dishes</i>
<i>like pho and</i> bun cha.

458
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:32,878
Even with pho,
the broth tastes different in each region.

459
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,680
DIFFERENT REGIONS HAVE DIFFERENT BROTHS

460
00:18:34,746 --> 00:18:37,249
In the central region,
there's a dish called <i>mi quang.</i>

461
00:18:37,316 --> 00:18:39,017
-<i>Mi quang</i>?
-Yes, <i>Mi quang</i>.

462
00:18:39,084 --> 00:18:42,187
It's similar to <i>bibim-guksu</i> in Korea.

463
00:18:42,254 --> 00:18:44,156
<i>-Bibim-guksu.</i>
-But then,

464
00:18:44,223 --> 00:18:46,792
sometimes it's made with shrimp,

465
00:18:46,859 --> 00:18:48,594
and sometimes it's pork.

466
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:50,996
It's a really good dish,
but I can rarely find a place

467
00:18:51,063 --> 00:18:52,931
that serves it in the north.

468
00:18:52,998 --> 00:18:57,736
So I want to recommend that you try that
if you ever visit central Vietnam.

469
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,638
In the southern area,

470
00:18:59,705 --> 00:19:02,741
there's a kind of set meal you can eat.

471
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:03,976
What's it called?

472
00:19:04,042 --> 00:19:06,712
<i>-Ca kho to.</i>
<i>-Ca kho to.</i>

473
00:19:06,778 --> 00:19:10,749
You put a piece of fish and the sauce
on top of some rice,

474
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:13,418
-and it's such a delicacy.
-I see.

475
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:15,854
That was a great tip.

476
00:19:15,921 --> 00:19:17,189
What's on the top shelf?

477
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:21,226
I see lots of Korean ingredients.
This must be <i>doenjang.</i>

478
00:19:21,293 --> 00:19:22,995
And kimchi, and <i>saeu-jeot,</i> salted shrimp.

479
00:19:23,061 --> 00:19:25,597
What's this, Manager Park?

480
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:27,332
-Soybean leaves.
-Soybean leaves.

481
00:19:27,399 --> 00:19:29,234
-Soybean leaves.
-<i>Doenjang</i>-marinated.

482
00:19:29,301 --> 00:19:31,637
I'm originally from Gyeongsang-do.

483
00:19:31,703 --> 00:19:34,039
-He's from Sancheong-gun.
-Sancheong-gun.

484
00:19:34,106 --> 00:19:35,841
And there, people prefer

485
00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:38,243
soybean leaves over perilla leaves.
They're more popular.

486
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:39,978
You must like Korean food, right?

487
00:19:40,045 --> 00:19:42,347
I'm a country man,
so I do love Korean food.

488
00:19:42,414 --> 00:19:43,615
I also like Chinese food.

489
00:19:43,682 --> 00:19:46,285
-Both <i>jjajangmyeon</i> and <i>jjamppong</i>.
-Chinese food.

490
00:19:46,351 --> 00:19:48,420
I'm not picky about food.

491
00:19:48,487 --> 00:19:50,389
-You aren't a picky eater.
-I see.

492
00:19:50,455 --> 00:19:52,958
What if you were to pick out
one best Korean dish?

493
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:58,363
I'm someone that people would
call old-fashioned, a boomer.

494
00:19:58,430 --> 00:19:59,898
So I always need soup with my meals.

495
00:19:59,965 --> 00:20:01,600
-Soup.
-He needs soup.

496
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:03,368
So I have sauces and ingredients for soup.

497
00:20:03,435 --> 00:20:06,505
-Here they are.
-Yes, you have dried anchovies for broth.

498
00:20:06,572 --> 00:20:08,640
He always needs soup.

499
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:12,344
What I craved the most in Vietnam was
freshwater <i>maeun-tang</i>, spicy fish stew.

500
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:15,547
I grew up near a river,
so I'm used to eating freshwater fish.

501
00:20:15,614 --> 00:20:17,282
-Freshwater <i>maeun-tang.</i>
<i>-Maeun-tang.</i>

502
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:20,018
A VERY SPECIAL INGREDIENT?

503
00:20:20,852 --> 00:20:23,121
-What are these?
-Those are…

504
00:20:23,188 --> 00:20:25,691
-Mandarinfish and catfish.
-Catfish?

505
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:28,493
CATFISH, MANDARINFISH

506
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:32,030
Since I'm here
with all these famous chefs,

507
00:20:32,097 --> 00:20:34,132
I want to eat something
I can't get in Vietnam,

508
00:20:34,199 --> 00:20:36,468
<i>maeun-tang</i> made
with mandarinfish or catfish.

509
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:40,472
I was hoping they'd do that.
That would be great.

510
00:20:40,539 --> 00:20:41,773
-Freshwater fish.
-That's new.

511
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,542
Is it our first time with freshwater fish?

512
00:20:43,609 --> 00:20:46,411
He's been craving
something he could only have here.

513
00:20:46,478 --> 00:20:49,915
He came ready with these.

514
00:20:49,982 --> 00:20:53,051
How do they eat <i>maeun-tang</i>
in your hometown?

515
00:20:53,118 --> 00:20:56,088
-With Korean mint and prickly ash powder.
-Korean mint.

516
00:20:56,154 --> 00:20:57,956
-Korean mint and prickly ash powder.
-That's it.

517
00:20:58,023 --> 00:21:00,425
Korean mint and prickly ash powder.

518
00:21:00,492 --> 00:21:03,895
Also, all these veggies.
You must like vegetables too.

519
00:21:03,962 --> 00:21:06,732
Lettuce. Is this morning glory?

520
00:21:06,798 --> 00:21:08,533
I'm a country man,

521
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:11,737
so I like making <i>ssam</i>
with leaves and <i>doenjang</i>.

522
00:21:11,803 --> 00:21:13,839
-Rice wraps.
-So I always keep leafy greens.

523
00:21:13,905 --> 00:21:16,942
-A coconut.
-What? It's a coconut.

524
00:21:17,009 --> 00:21:18,010
A coconut?

525
00:21:18,076 --> 00:21:19,111
Durian.

526
00:21:19,177 --> 00:21:21,880
-Durian? I love durian!
-Durian. It's already smelly.

527
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:27,853
I serve coconut as a welcome drink
when I have guests over.

528
00:21:27,919 --> 00:21:29,588
-Green papaya.
-That's a papaya.

529
00:21:29,655 --> 00:21:31,089
-A papaya.
-Papaya?

530
00:21:31,156 --> 00:21:32,257
That's really good.

531
00:21:32,324 --> 00:21:34,159
-Makes great som tam.
-Often eaten in Southeast Asia.

532
00:21:34,226 --> 00:21:36,495
To the freezer.

533
00:21:36,561 --> 00:21:39,131
There's some meat. Do you also enjoy meat?

534
00:21:39,197 --> 00:21:41,767
I see some beef, as well as pork.

535
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:44,836
Pork is much more delicious
than beef in Vietnam.

536
00:21:44,903 --> 00:21:46,505
So I usually eat pork,

537
00:21:46,571 --> 00:21:48,307
but I try to stick to a leaner cut.

538
00:21:48,373 --> 00:21:50,575
But you only eat beef
when you eat with me.

539
00:21:51,076 --> 00:21:52,110
AWKWARD HANG-SEO

540
00:21:52,177 --> 00:21:55,314
I took a look
at the shelf-stable ingredients

541
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:57,316
and saw lots of Vietnamese ingredients.

542
00:21:57,382 --> 00:22:00,185
I see lots of Vietnamese writing.

543
00:22:00,252 --> 00:22:02,521
Also some rice paper.

544
00:22:02,587 --> 00:22:06,792
These remind me of glass noodles.
And rice noodles.

545
00:22:06,858 --> 00:22:09,895
-He likes noodles too.
-He likes noodles.

546
00:22:09,961 --> 00:22:11,663
He has lots of rice noodles.

547
00:22:11,730 --> 00:22:15,701
That's all for Manager Park's fridge!

548
00:22:17,569 --> 00:22:21,606
And now, it's time to find out
what his orders are.

549
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,642
These are Manager Park Hang-seo's orders!

550
00:22:23,709 --> 00:22:26,445
2026 Rice-dink FAFA World Cup.

551
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,412
FAFA World Cup.

552
00:22:27,479 --> 00:22:31,450
-It's not FIFA, but FAFA World Cup.
-FAFA?

553
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:33,352
I've had my share of Vietnamese food,

554
00:22:33,418 --> 00:22:36,488
but of course,
I'm always going to miss Korean food.

555
00:22:36,555 --> 00:22:40,058
So I wanted a Vietnamese dish
with a touch of Korean flavor,

556
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:41,960
since I'm here with these great chefs.

557
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:43,862
I CORDIALLY ASK OF YOU

558
00:22:43,929 --> 00:22:45,964
A Vietnamese dish with a touch of Korea.

559
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:48,233
-That's what it is.
-Is that too hard?

560
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:49,668
Let's find out the second order.

561
00:22:49,735 --> 00:22:53,772
Manager Park's next order
is 2026 Freshwater FISH World Cup.

562
00:22:53,839 --> 00:22:54,940
-Mandarinfish.
-Freshwater FISH.

563
00:22:55,006 --> 00:22:55,941
FISH World Cup.

564
00:22:56,007 --> 00:22:58,343
I brought the catfish and mandarinfish

565
00:22:58,410 --> 00:22:59,978
because I haven't had them recently.

566
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:01,580
I get it when I'm out of the city.

567
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:05,417
I wanted to have that taste
of my hometown,

568
00:23:05,484 --> 00:23:09,121
so the two things you must use
are Korean mint and prickly ash powder.

569
00:23:09,187 --> 00:23:10,622
You need those.

570
00:23:10,689 --> 00:23:12,791
It's time to decide the contenders.

571
00:23:12,858 --> 00:23:14,726
It's Chef Moon-jung's first time here,

572
00:23:14,793 --> 00:23:16,595
so you can choose first.

573
00:23:16,661 --> 00:23:19,331
-I'm in.
-You are? Which one will you take?

574
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:23,068
-The 2026 Freshwater FISH World Cup.
-Freshwater fish.

575
00:23:23,135 --> 00:23:24,403
-Fish.
-Freshwater fish?

576
00:23:24,469 --> 00:23:26,538
-In China…
-There are lots of freshwater fish dishes.

577
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:28,640
…there are many freshwater fish dishes.

578
00:23:28,707 --> 00:23:31,643
So I'll use that freshwater fish

579
00:23:32,210 --> 00:23:34,146
and slay everything.

580
00:23:34,379 --> 00:23:35,947
SLAY, SLAY

581
00:23:36,181 --> 00:23:37,783
CLAPPING LIKE A SEAL

582
00:23:37,849 --> 00:23:41,820
I wonder what Eun-yeong will choose to do.

583
00:23:41,887 --> 00:23:45,624
-Shouldn't you slay with her?
-Yes, she should jump in.

584
00:23:45,690 --> 00:23:46,658
-No way.
-Yes?

585
00:23:46,725 --> 00:23:48,894
Not only do many people want to see this,

586
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:53,398
but I've also wanted
to go up against Chef Moon-jung.

587
00:23:53,465 --> 00:23:57,436
So I'll also join the round,
2026 Freshwater FISH World Cup.

588
00:23:57,602 --> 00:23:59,137
ATTA GIRL

589
00:23:59,204 --> 00:24:00,372
The fight is on.

590
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:05,010
Witch With a Wok
versus Goddess of Chinese Cuisine.

591
00:24:05,076 --> 00:24:07,045
I've never mentioned it before,

592
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:10,115
but I'm quite a soccer fan.

593
00:24:10,182 --> 00:24:14,286
-I'll join the FAFA World Cup.
-FAFA World Cup.

594
00:24:14,352 --> 00:24:16,121
-You've won five times in a row.
-Five times?

595
00:24:16,188 --> 00:24:19,291
He has the most stars right now,
so it might be a tough fight.

596
00:24:19,357 --> 00:24:20,625
Who wants to jump in?

597
00:24:20,692 --> 00:24:22,861
Who'll fight Jong-won?

598
00:24:22,928 --> 00:24:24,896
-I'll go.
-I knew it.

599
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:26,798
That's Sung-jun, full of vigor.

600
00:24:26,865 --> 00:24:28,700
Just like Jong-won,

601
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:31,803
-I'm also on a winning streak. Three wins.
-That's true.

602
00:24:31,870 --> 00:24:34,840
I'm probably the only one
who can stop him.

603
00:24:34,906 --> 00:24:37,275
-Two chefs with winning streaks.
-I'll stop him.

604
00:24:37,342 --> 00:24:40,212
The chefs on winning streaks
are up against each other.

605
00:24:40,278 --> 00:24:45,584
Then let us begin
the 2026 Rice-dink FAFA World Cup!

606
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:53,492
<i>The first round of cook-off</i>
<i>with Manager Park's ingredients.</i>

607
00:24:53,558 --> 00:24:55,327
He's been on a roll lately!

608
00:24:55,393 --> 00:24:58,830
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i>'s sole striker,
Son Jong-won.

609
00:24:58,897 --> 00:25:01,132
Versus the man who has been
following him like a shadow.

610
00:25:01,199 --> 00:25:05,370
Assigned to man-mark Jong-won,
Kwon Sung-jun.

611
00:25:05,437 --> 00:25:06,671
Assigned to Jong-won.

612
00:25:06,738 --> 00:25:10,108
Two chefs who have been doing well lately
are up against each other.

613
00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:11,810
Jong-won has won five times in a row.

614
00:25:11,877 --> 00:25:13,712
Sung-jun has won three times in a row.

615
00:25:13,778 --> 00:25:15,180
I don't believe it either.

616
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:18,183
I don't understand
how I won three times in a row.

617
00:25:18,250 --> 00:25:20,819
But I lost a bit of weight,
which made me feel lighter.

618
00:25:20,886 --> 00:25:22,020
JEALOUS

619
00:25:22,087 --> 00:25:23,188
I can move much faster now,

620
00:25:23,255 --> 00:25:25,023
so I can do much more in 15 minutes.

621
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:26,892
He reminds me of Kim Min-jae.

622
00:25:26,958 --> 00:25:28,527
-His hairstyle too.
-I can see that.

623
00:25:28,593 --> 00:25:29,961
And we're both from Naples.

624
00:25:30,195 --> 00:25:31,863
THE TWO SOCCER MANAGERS AGREE

625
00:25:31,930 --> 00:25:33,765
Chef Sung-jun said something like this.

626
00:25:33,832 --> 00:25:35,066
What? What did I say?

627
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:36,701
"I don't know about anything else,

628
00:25:36,768 --> 00:25:39,004
but I know I'm a better soccer player
than Jong-won."

629
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:40,539
A-HA!

630
00:25:40,605 --> 00:25:42,307
Were you a good soccer player?

631
00:25:42,374 --> 00:25:44,242
-I played a bit in my neighborhood.
-His neighborhood?

632
00:25:44,309 --> 00:25:46,311
I played as a shadow striker.

633
00:25:46,845 --> 00:25:48,046
PFFT

634
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:49,881
First, I'd hide myself completely,

635
00:25:49,948 --> 00:25:52,717
and I was always good
at spotting a chance to score.

636
00:25:52,784 --> 00:25:54,452
I'm originally from Nowon-gu,

637
00:25:54,519 --> 00:25:56,521
-so I was known as Nowon-gu's Inzaghi.
-Nowon-gu's Inzaghi.

638
00:25:56,588 --> 00:25:58,123
LOL…

639
00:25:58,189 --> 00:26:02,127
He keeps laughing at every word you say.

640
00:26:02,193 --> 00:26:03,862
Anything like that, Jong-won?

641
00:26:03,929 --> 00:26:05,330
I had a nickname too.

642
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:06,398
HOLDING IN CHECK

643
00:26:06,464 --> 00:26:07,899
Back in high school, I was called

644
00:26:07,966 --> 00:26:09,334
Mississippi's Jung-hwan.

645
00:26:09,401 --> 00:26:10,802
-Mississippi's Jung-hwan?
-Mississippi's Jung-hwan?

646
00:26:10,869 --> 00:26:12,003
Mississippi's Jung-hwan?

647
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:14,639
I went to high school in the US,

648
00:26:14,706 --> 00:26:16,474
and I was a part
of the school's varsity team

649
00:26:16,541 --> 00:26:18,476
-as the captain.
-What?

650
00:26:18,543 --> 00:26:20,312
-The varsity captain?
-That's awesome.

651
00:26:20,378 --> 00:26:21,313
That means you're good.

652
00:26:21,379 --> 00:26:23,214
-He played in his neighborhood.
-Different levels.

653
00:26:23,281 --> 00:26:25,383
-He was the captain too.
-Wait, what?

654
00:26:25,450 --> 00:26:27,552
I was a striker,

655
00:26:27,619 --> 00:26:29,521
and my shirt number was 19.

656
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:31,456
-Right.
-Jung-hwan's number.

657
00:26:31,523 --> 00:26:32,924
JUNG-HWAN'S SHIRT NUMBER

658
00:26:32,991 --> 00:26:36,461
-I always knew he'd make it big.
-There's a connection.

659
00:26:36,528 --> 00:26:38,263
-He's actually Ahn Jong-won.
-He is?

660
00:26:38,330 --> 00:26:40,632
-Not Son Jong-won.
-"Ahn Jong-won."

661
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:42,367
Mississippi's Jung-hwan

662
00:26:42,434 --> 00:26:45,737
-and Nowon-gu's Inzaghi are up.
-Nowon-gu's Inzaghi.

663
00:26:45,804 --> 00:26:50,141
You're about to make
a Vietnamese dish with a touch of Korea.

664
00:26:50,208 --> 00:26:54,412
-So it's an emergency for both chefs.
-Why?

665
00:26:54,479 --> 00:26:57,415
-They've never been to Vietnam.
-What?

666
00:26:57,482 --> 00:26:58,450
-Really?
-Really?

667
00:26:58,516 --> 00:27:00,051
-Never been there.
-I should've gone.

668
00:27:00,118 --> 00:27:02,354
-I should've jumped in.
-I've been there ten times.

669
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:04,122
But Chef Sung-jun said

670
00:27:04,189 --> 00:27:06,391
he has the upper hand in this round.

671
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,526
I really love Vietnamese food,

672
00:27:08,593 --> 00:27:11,062
and I often made it as the staff meal.

673
00:27:11,129 --> 00:27:12,597
He has no staff, though.

674
00:27:12,664 --> 00:27:14,833
-You don't have any employees.
-Not at my place.

675
00:27:14,899 --> 00:27:16,501
So when you ate alone?

676
00:27:16,568 --> 00:27:19,371
It was a meal for one!

677
00:27:19,437 --> 00:27:21,473
Not my current place,
but the restaurant before.

678
00:27:21,539 --> 00:27:23,208
-Before?
-From the place before.

679
00:27:23,274 --> 00:27:24,109
I made it often.

680
00:27:24,175 --> 00:27:26,177
How many people were there
in your previous restaurant?

681
00:27:26,244 --> 00:27:28,680
There were quite a few.

682
00:27:28,747 --> 00:27:29,648
Four to five people.

683
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:31,516
HOW MODEST

684
00:27:31,583 --> 00:27:34,586
-That's only as big as my family!
-Really?

685
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:37,188
I also really love Vietnamese food,

686
00:27:37,255 --> 00:27:39,090
and pho is my go-to hangover cure.

687
00:27:40,091 --> 00:27:41,059
That's a great cure.

688
00:27:41,126 --> 00:27:42,060
I eat it quite often.

689
00:27:42,127 --> 00:27:46,598
Also, I had to make the staff meals
for two restaurants at once,

690
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:47,966
which amounted to 70 people.

691
00:27:48,033 --> 00:27:49,701
-Seventy?
-Yes, the entire staff.

692
00:27:49,768 --> 00:27:51,069
I often made Vietnamese food.

693
00:27:51,136 --> 00:27:52,737
That's what we call a staff meal.

694
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:54,372
And finally, back in college,

695
00:27:54,439 --> 00:27:55,840
my roommate was Vietnamese.

696
00:27:56,074 --> 00:27:57,175
JONG-WON'S DECISIVE GOAL

697
00:27:57,242 --> 00:27:59,878
-If his roommate was Vietnamese…
-He'd know the culture more.

698
00:28:00,145 --> 00:28:01,713
DOING HIS BEST TO DENY IT

699
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:05,016
I can probably say
that Vietnam is my second hometown.

700
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:07,285
Wait, didn't you say it was Hong Kong?

701
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:09,988
You said it was Hong Kong last time.

702
00:28:10,055 --> 00:28:11,423
He's never even been there.

703
00:28:11,489 --> 00:28:13,058
Home is where your heart is.

704
00:28:13,124 --> 00:28:15,560
I believe where my heart is right now
is my hometown.

705
00:28:16,394 --> 00:28:18,997
CHEF JONG-WON'S INGREDIENTS:
BEEF TENDERLOIN, PORK BELLY, SHRIMP

706
00:28:19,064 --> 00:28:21,666
COCONUT, COCONUT MILK, CILANTRO,
CABBAGE, GREEN PAPAYA, CARROT, AND MORE

707
00:28:21,733 --> 00:28:24,069
What are you making, Chef Jong-won?

708
00:28:24,436 --> 00:28:25,270
HAH…

709
00:28:25,770 --> 00:28:26,738
Well…

710
00:28:26,805 --> 00:28:27,772
What's he doing?

711
00:28:27,839 --> 00:28:29,340
Wait, are you going to dance?

712
00:28:29,908 --> 00:28:31,042
First of all,

713
00:28:31,109 --> 00:28:35,346
I prepared a Vietnamese dish
that has a Korean twist.

714
00:28:35,413 --> 00:28:38,550
I think Korean <i>jeon</i>
and Vietnamese <i>banh xeo </i>are similar.

715
00:28:38,616 --> 00:28:40,752
-That's true.
<i>-Banh xeo</i> is good.

716
00:28:40,819 --> 00:28:42,687
Since Manager Park is here,

717
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:45,223
I want to show my support
for the upcoming World Cup.

718
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:47,392
I'm basically making <i>banh xeo</i>

719
00:28:47,459 --> 00:28:49,360
filled with <i>jeyuk-bokkeum,</i>
stir-fried pork,

720
00:28:49,427 --> 00:28:51,629
as well as shrimp and Korean mint,

721
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:53,498
so it'll have many different flavors.

722
00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:55,867
You also said
you always have soup with your food,

723
00:28:55,934 --> 00:28:58,336
so I want to serve
the broth for pho on the side

724
00:28:58,403 --> 00:29:01,906
-with some <i>tteok</i>, rice cake.
-With <i>tteok</i>?

725
00:29:01,973 --> 00:29:04,676
I also want to make a coconut beverage.

726
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:05,777
A coconut beverage?

727
00:29:05,844 --> 00:29:07,278
I'm excited.

728
00:29:07,345 --> 00:29:10,749
He's making Vietnamese <i>jeon</i>
with a Korean twist.

729
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:13,885
CHEF KWON-ZAGHI'S INGREDIENTS:
PORK NECK, PORK BELLY, SHRIMP

730
00:29:13,952 --> 00:29:16,254
QUAIL EGG, NAPA CABBAGE, MORNING GLORY,
BEAN SPROUTS, MUKEUNJI, AND MORE

731
00:29:16,321 --> 00:29:18,723
What are you making, Chef Sung-jun?

732
00:29:18,790 --> 00:29:20,792
What I'm going to make is

733
00:29:20,859 --> 00:29:22,527
Isn't This the Mi Quang You Wanted?

734
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:24,996
GIGGLE

735
00:29:25,063 --> 00:29:26,397
Isn't This the Mi Quang You Wanted?

736
00:29:26,464 --> 00:29:27,298
BOING

737
00:29:27,699 --> 00:29:29,267
INVADING HIS SOLO SHOT

738
00:29:29,334 --> 00:29:31,336
That's Kyung-hwan's tagline.

739
00:29:31,402 --> 00:29:32,604
What is it exactly?

740
00:29:32,670 --> 00:29:34,305
Isn't This the Mi Quang You Wanted?

741
00:29:34,372 --> 00:29:37,742
-<i>Mi quang!</i>
-"Isn't This the Mi Quang You Wanted?"

742
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:40,245
-You said you really like <i>mi quang.</i>
<i>-Mi quang.</i>

743
00:29:40,311 --> 00:29:41,646
Well, I've never tried it.

744
00:29:42,213 --> 00:29:44,516
But I asked ChatGPT

745
00:29:44,582 --> 00:29:46,317
and found the recipe to prepare this dish.

746
00:29:46,384 --> 00:29:47,585
Wait a minute…

747
00:29:47,652 --> 00:29:49,788
To add a bit of Korean flavor,

748
00:29:49,854 --> 00:29:51,956
I'm going to use
<i>doenjang </i>and anchovy broth.

749
00:29:52,023 --> 00:29:53,658
Those are my Korean touches.

750
00:29:53,725 --> 00:29:54,859
I'm also making <i>cha gio</i>

751
00:29:54,926 --> 00:29:57,428
with <i>mukeunji</i>, aged kimchi.

752
00:29:57,495 --> 00:29:58,563
<i>Mukeunji cha gio.</i>

753
00:29:58,630 --> 00:29:59,697
-That sounds good.
-Also,

754
00:29:59,764 --> 00:30:02,333
I'm going to serve
stir-fried morning glory.

755
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,802
-I see.
-Three dishes.

756
00:30:03,868 --> 00:30:05,370
So what is it called again?

757
00:30:05,436 --> 00:30:06,437
Isn't This the <i>Mi Quang</i> You Wanted?

758
00:30:06,871 --> 00:30:08,473
AVOIDS HIM IN ADVANCE

759
00:30:09,674 --> 00:30:10,508
WHERE'D HE GO?

760
00:30:10,575 --> 00:30:12,143
Why do you travel that far?

761
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:15,113
-What's he doing?
-They're both up for a big challenge.

762
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:17,816
A battle between banh xeo and mi quang.

763
00:30:17,882 --> 00:30:19,551
Let us begin their cook-off.

764
00:30:20,185 --> 00:30:23,488
2026 Rice-dink FAFA World Cup.

765
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:26,224
<i>We need to see</i>
<i>the </i><i>dishes </i><i>out </i><i>in 15 minutes.</i>

766
00:30:26,291 --> 00:30:28,393
He's here to score his sixth goal in a row

767
00:30:28,459 --> 00:30:30,662
to become the MVP of the show.

768
00:30:30,728 --> 00:30:33,364
Mississippi's Jung-hwan,
Chef Son Jong-won.

769
00:30:33,798 --> 00:30:35,567
LOVING IT

770
00:30:35,633 --> 00:30:39,003
Here to tackle Jong-won down today,

771
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:42,674
Nowon-gu's Inzaghi, Chef Kwon Sung-jun.

772
00:30:42,740 --> 00:30:46,177
Who's going to keep their winning streak
after the FAFA World Cup?

773
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:50,315
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

774
00:30:53,051 --> 00:30:55,320
WHAT'S THE FIRST MOVE
FOR MISSISSIPPI'S JUNG-HWAN?

775
00:30:55,386 --> 00:30:57,121
Poong, help me with the coconut.

776
00:30:57,188 --> 00:30:59,924
-Two chefs with winning streaks are up.
-Peel it for me.

777
00:31:00,191 --> 00:31:01,860
I BELIEVE IN YOU!

778
00:31:02,093 --> 00:31:03,595
WATER, VINEGAR, SUGAR

779
00:31:04,195 --> 00:31:05,864
ADD CILANTRO

780
00:31:05,930 --> 00:31:07,432
BOILING PICKLING JUICE

781
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:09,234
CABBAGE

782
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:10,835
INTO THE STEAMER

783
00:31:10,902 --> 00:31:13,071
Are you slicing the papaya?

784
00:31:13,137 --> 00:31:15,306
Yes, I'm trying to make papaya pickles.

785
00:31:15,373 --> 00:31:17,041
-Papaya pickles.
-Pickles.

786
00:31:17,108 --> 00:31:18,743
1. JULIENNE PAPAYA, CARROT, ONION
AND PICKLE

787
00:31:19,377 --> 00:31:21,379
I've never had papaya pickles.

788
00:31:21,446 --> 00:31:22,881
What are you doing, Poong?

789
00:31:22,947 --> 00:31:24,115
He asked me to peel the coconut.

790
00:31:24,182 --> 00:31:25,817
Are you using it to cook?

791
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,552
He said he was going to make a beverage.

792
00:31:27,619 --> 00:31:28,920
A coconut beverage.

793
00:31:32,056 --> 00:31:33,524
HUH? HE'S…

794
00:31:33,591 --> 00:31:35,426
-Do you know how to do it?
-Poong is at it.

795
00:31:35,493 --> 00:31:36,828
THE WATER IS ABOUT TO SPILL OUT

796
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:38,096
-What now?
-Did you get it?

797
00:31:38,162 --> 00:31:41,266
-Peel it and give me the water.
-Peel it? How do you peel it?

798
00:31:41,332 --> 00:31:43,201
-Peel it and give me the water.
-The water?

799
00:31:43,268 --> 00:31:45,236
-Make a hole on top.
-Cut it on the top.

800
00:31:45,303 --> 00:31:46,404
So just the water?

801
00:31:46,471 --> 00:31:48,206
-I'm using the shell too.
-You are?

802
00:31:48,273 --> 00:31:50,441
-Do I cut it like this?
-It's already ruined.

803
00:31:50,508 --> 00:31:52,610
That means I have to leave it whole.

804
00:31:52,677 --> 00:31:55,046
-Cut the top.
-Why did you put him up for that?

805
00:31:55,113 --> 00:31:57,482
Wait, I didn't know
you were using the shell.

806
00:31:58,349 --> 00:32:00,551
MAKING A HOLE ON THE TOP

807
00:32:01,286 --> 00:32:03,421
KIM POONG THE TROUBLESHOOTER

808
00:32:03,655 --> 00:32:05,990
NICE ASSIST

809
00:32:06,057 --> 00:32:09,827
The winning streak will continue
for one of you, but not the other.

810
00:32:10,628 --> 00:32:12,130
He's using meat. Is that pork?

811
00:32:12,196 --> 00:32:13,331
Yes, it's pork.

812
00:32:13,932 --> 00:32:15,099
What's that?

813
00:32:15,166 --> 00:32:16,768
-Turmeric.
-Turmeric.

814
00:32:16,834 --> 00:32:18,903
-You're using turmeric on pork?
-Yes.

815
00:32:18,970 --> 00:32:21,139
<i>Mi quang</i> is made with lots of turmeric.

816
00:32:21,205 --> 00:32:22,040
ANCHOVY BROTH PACK

817
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:23,474
STAR ANISE

818
00:32:24,876 --> 00:32:25,710
QUAIL EGG

819
00:32:27,412 --> 00:32:29,514
LOTS OF SPICES AND CONDIMENTS
FOR SOUTHEAST ASIAN FOOD

820
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:31,482
ADDING OYSTER SAUCE TO THE PORK NECK

821
00:32:31,549 --> 00:32:33,451
He's cooking shrimp with the pork.

822
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:35,787
STIR-FRYING WITH HIS HAND

823
00:32:35,853 --> 00:32:38,222
Sung-jun is now stir-frying with his hand.

824
00:32:38,289 --> 00:32:39,757
ADDING CHOP CHOP ONION FOR FAFA

825
00:32:40,325 --> 00:32:42,026
WHIPPED UP IN A FLASH

826
00:32:42,093 --> 00:32:44,929
Jong-won will be making
something similar to <i>jeon</i>.

827
00:32:44,996 --> 00:32:46,264
BAY LEAF, CONDIMENTS

828
00:32:46,331 --> 00:32:48,399
But I don't see him making <i>jeon</i> yet.

829
00:32:48,466 --> 00:32:50,168
He also uses meat.

830
00:32:50,935 --> 00:32:52,637
TWO SPOONS OF MINCED GARLIC

831
00:32:52,704 --> 00:32:54,672
You're using beef, right?

832
00:32:54,739 --> 00:32:57,208
-Yes. It's beef.
-Beef.

833
00:32:57,275 --> 00:32:58,409
It's for the broth.

834
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:01,346
UP THE FLAVOR BY STIR-FRYING

835
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:03,214
Four minutes have gone by.

836
00:33:03,281 --> 00:33:05,950
Things seem smoother for Chef Sung-jun.

837
00:33:06,017 --> 00:33:07,785
He's smooth sailing.

838
00:33:07,852 --> 00:33:11,856
He found his composure
after consecutive wins.

839
00:33:11,923 --> 00:33:15,793
After all, he was the winner
of <i>Culinary Class Wars S1.</i>

840
00:33:16,294 --> 00:33:17,395
Right.

841
00:33:17,462 --> 00:33:19,163
-He won, right?
-Yes.

842
00:33:19,530 --> 00:33:21,366
DON'T FORGET!

843
00:33:21,632 --> 00:33:25,937
1. ADD NAPA CABBAGE AND WATER
TO PORK AND SHRIMP AND BOIL

844
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:27,405
Sung-jun, is that stew?

845
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:29,941
-Stew?
-No, it's the broth for <i>mi quang</i>.

846
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:32,877
-He's using morning glory.
-He grabs morning glory.

847
00:33:33,644 --> 00:33:35,780
Morning glory.

848
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:38,149
Will he add seasoning and mix it?

849
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:39,650
Doh!

850
00:33:39,717 --> 00:33:40,685
I need nuoc mam.

851
00:33:40,752 --> 00:33:42,453
-Nuoc mam? Over here.
-It's an emergency.

852
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:43,588
-An emergency?
-Why?

853
00:33:43,654 --> 00:33:44,822
-It's that sauce.
-Nuoc mam.

854
00:33:44,889 --> 00:33:47,692
-Manager Park's favorite, right?
-Yes.

855
00:33:47,759 --> 00:33:50,261
-Was it nugu oc?
-Nuoc mam.

856
00:33:50,328 --> 00:33:51,896
-Nuoc mam.
-Nuoc mam. That's the sauce.

857
00:33:52,463 --> 00:33:54,999
-It's starting to smell like Vietnam.
-Already?

858
00:33:55,066 --> 00:33:56,000
SNIFF!

859
00:33:56,067 --> 00:33:57,035
Yes, I can smell it too.

860
00:33:57,101 --> 00:34:00,204
I'm starting to smell it.
It feels like Vietnam.

861
00:34:00,271 --> 00:34:02,774
I'm using lots of spices to make broth.

862
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:04,709
It smells like Hanoi.

863
00:34:04,776 --> 00:34:06,077
It smells like a pho place.

864
00:34:06,344 --> 00:34:07,645
HOPEFUL

865
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:09,947
How do you say "delicious" in Vietnamese?

866
00:34:10,014 --> 00:34:12,050
<i>-Aroi.</i>
<i>-Aroi.</i>

867
00:34:12,116 --> 00:34:13,885
THAT'S THAI, ACTUALLY

868
00:34:13,951 --> 00:34:16,054
"Enjoy your meal" is <i>xin mời</i>.

869
00:34:16,254 --> 00:34:17,755
AMY LEARNS A FOREIGN PHRASE!

870
00:34:17,822 --> 00:34:19,657
-<i>Xin mời.</i>
-I see.

871
00:34:19,957 --> 00:34:21,125
BEGINS TO PREP BANH XEO FILLINGS

872
00:34:21,659 --> 00:34:27,565
2. MIX SHRIMP, SOY SAUCE, BEAN SPROUTS,
GARLIC POWDER, AND ONION FOR FILLING

873
00:34:27,765 --> 00:34:29,267
WHAT DOES HE NEED NEXT?

874
00:34:29,333 --> 00:34:30,668
Nuoc mam.

875
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:32,937
Nuoc mam. Where's the nuoc mam?

876
00:34:33,004 --> 00:34:34,639
HE CAUSED A SCENE AND TOOK IT

877
00:34:34,705 --> 00:34:35,973
It's an emergency.

878
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:38,476
I'M TAKING IT BACK

879
00:34:38,876 --> 00:34:40,978
AT EASE

880
00:34:41,045 --> 00:34:43,381
It looks like
Chef Jong-won is doing a lot.

881
00:34:43,448 --> 00:34:47,618
He's cooking the shrimp and bean sprouts
that'll fill the <i>banh xeo</i>.

882
00:34:47,685 --> 00:34:48,519
STIR-FRY

883
00:34:49,654 --> 00:34:51,222
What was that? Whoa!

884
00:34:51,823 --> 00:34:54,358
A SUDDEN FIRE SHOW

885
00:34:54,892 --> 00:34:56,227
It's ablaze!

886
00:34:56,294 --> 00:34:57,762
-Your hair.
-Hair!

887
00:34:57,829 --> 00:34:59,230
EVERYONE IS WORKED UP

888
00:34:59,297 --> 00:35:00,932
-Your hair!
-Your hair might burn!

889
00:35:01,466 --> 00:35:03,367
HE EVEN HAS TIME TO TEASE THEM

890
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:05,703
-It's on your hair!
-Your hair's burning!

891
00:35:05,770 --> 00:35:08,639
-Watch your hair!
-You'll burn your hair! Watch out!

892
00:35:08,706 --> 00:35:12,276
-Your hair's on fire!
-Your bangs are burnt!

893
00:35:13,277 --> 00:35:15,113
DOESN'T FALL FOR IT

894
00:35:15,179 --> 00:35:16,681
-It smells burnt.
-You almost lost your bangs.

895
00:35:16,747 --> 00:35:18,149
DISAPPOINTED THAT HE DOESN'T BUY IT

896
00:35:18,216 --> 00:35:21,986
-As we speak, is Sung-jun grinding meat?
-Yes.

897
00:35:22,053 --> 00:35:22,987
BEAN SPROUTS

898
00:35:23,054 --> 00:35:25,957
I think he's grinding meat
with <i>mukeunji</i> to make <i>cha gio</i>.

899
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:27,391
You're grinding it with <i>mukeunji?</i>

900
00:35:27,458 --> 00:35:29,427
He's adding oyster sauce too.

901
00:35:29,494 --> 00:35:30,862
And napa cabbage.

902
00:35:30,928 --> 00:35:32,663
-Is there <i>mukeunji</i> too?
-Yes.

903
00:35:32,730 --> 00:35:35,266
The cabbage isn't crushed.
Chop it a little first.

904
00:35:35,333 --> 00:35:36,767
It's good enough.

905
00:35:36,834 --> 00:35:38,102
-Rice paper.
-Yes.

906
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:40,438
-He's making <i>cha gio.</i>
<i>-Cha gio.</i>

907
00:35:40,505 --> 00:35:41,839
Why is it red, though?

908
00:35:41,906 --> 00:35:43,841
-Because of the <i>mukeunji.</i>
-The <i>mukeunji?</i>

909
00:35:43,908 --> 00:35:45,243
Will you steam those?

910
00:35:45,309 --> 00:35:47,044
-Deep-fry.
-You'll deep-fry them?

911
00:35:47,111 --> 00:35:50,148
Right. It's <i>cha gio</i>,
so he has to deep-fry it.

912
00:35:50,214 --> 00:35:52,517
There are nine minutes left.

913
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:54,318
NOTICES SOMETHING

914
00:35:55,419 --> 00:35:56,521
Wouldn't the handle be too hot?

915
00:35:56,587 --> 00:35:59,223
-What? That?
-Over there. That handle.

916
00:35:59,290 --> 00:36:01,659
-Down there. Yes.
-Right here? Down here?

917
00:36:01,726 --> 00:36:03,327
-It's fine.
-He says it's fine.

918
00:36:03,394 --> 00:36:04,762
-It's fine.
-It's all right.

919
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:06,664
He has no time to mind that.

920
00:36:06,731 --> 00:36:09,467
-Moon-jung watches the cook-off carefully.
-Yes, I need to.

921
00:36:09,534 --> 00:36:12,003
-Yes.
-Because she has to go next.

922
00:36:12,069 --> 00:36:13,738
-She's never done it.
-She's nervous.

923
00:36:13,804 --> 00:36:16,340
She's hiding right behind Poong.

924
00:36:16,407 --> 00:36:18,142
Why did it have to be him?

925
00:36:18,376 --> 00:36:19,944
CHOSE THE WRONG ONE AS HER SUPERIOR

926
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,246
It looks like
Chef Jong-won is doing a lot.

927
00:36:22,613 --> 00:36:26,317
3. MIX RED PEPPER POWDER, SUGAR,
GARLIC, SOY SAUCE, GREEN ONION, ONION

928
00:36:26,717 --> 00:36:27,952
AND PORK BELLY?

929
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:30,855
-What's Jong-won making?
-<i>Jeyuk-bokkeum.</i>

930
00:36:30,922 --> 00:36:32,623
-Spicy stir-fried pork?
-Yes.

931
00:36:33,758 --> 00:36:36,794
STIR-FRYING THE PORK RIGHT AWAY

932
00:36:37,795 --> 00:36:39,063
-Nuoc mam?
-Nuoc mam.

933
00:36:39,130 --> 00:36:43,100
Actually, soy sauce
is rarely ever used in Vietnam.

934
00:36:43,167 --> 00:36:47,038
It's starting to smell
a bit like nuoc mam.

935
00:36:47,838 --> 00:36:49,874
SUNG-JUN COOKS THIN GLASS NOODLES

936
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:51,776
TURMERIC BROTH

937
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,778
Is that <i>saeu-jeot</i>, salted shrimp?

938
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:57,582
Chef Sung-jun is deep-frying shrimp paste
made with flour and <i>saeu-jeot</i>.

939
00:36:57,648 --> 00:36:59,884
-He's frying salted shrimp.
-Salted shrimp?

940
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:01,252
That's going to be so salty.

941
00:37:01,319 --> 00:37:03,754
It'll still be overly salty
even after washing it

942
00:37:03,821 --> 00:37:05,256
-in water and whatnot.
-There's no point.

943
00:37:05,323 --> 00:37:07,825
Wait, is it because <i>cha gio</i>
sounds like "Is this salty?"

944
00:37:07,892 --> 00:37:10,494
-<i>Cha gio</i>?
-Is this <i>jjajyo</i>?

945
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:12,363
-Is it salty?
-It'll be very salty.

946
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:15,066
Stay calm.

947
00:37:15,132 --> 00:37:17,468
-Stay calm.
-Who are you telling that to?

948
00:37:17,535 --> 00:37:19,237
-Myself.
-Right.

949
00:37:19,303 --> 00:37:21,439
Stay calm. This is an important moment.

950
00:37:21,505 --> 00:37:23,407
What are you making, Chef Sung-jun?

951
00:37:23,474 --> 00:37:24,642
<i>Cha gio</i> sauce.

952
00:37:24,709 --> 00:37:25,843
-<i>Cha gio</i> sauce.
-<i>Cha gio</i> sauce.

953
00:37:25,910 --> 00:37:27,345
It's the dip.

954
00:37:27,411 --> 00:37:30,615
The sauce is quite salty too, right?
It must be.

955
00:37:30,681 --> 00:37:32,316
He's making <i>cha gio</i>
to make something salty.

956
00:37:32,617 --> 00:37:34,285
SMACK…

957
00:37:34,352 --> 00:37:35,486
Too salty.

958
00:37:35,553 --> 00:37:37,888
-Even the sauce is salty.
-The sauce is salty too!

959
00:37:37,955 --> 00:37:38,990
IT'S REAL SALTY, ISN'T IT?

960
00:37:39,056 --> 00:37:41,058
Sung-jun takes the noodles out.

961
00:37:41,959 --> 00:37:42,893
That's hot.

962
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,195
A BRIEF FUSS

963
00:37:45,129 --> 00:37:46,897
SETS IT ASIDE FOR A MOMENT

964
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:48,199
LOOKING SERIOUS

965
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:50,268
Everyone, watch out!

966
00:37:50,334 --> 00:37:51,702
Be careful.

967
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:54,405
WILL HE PUT ON A FIRE SHOW?

968
00:37:54,772 --> 00:37:56,374
DROPPING MORNING GLORY

969
00:38:01,012 --> 00:38:02,680
The morning glory looks delicious.

970
00:38:02,913 --> 00:38:05,116
BUT NOTHING HAPPENED

971
00:38:05,182 --> 00:38:06,851
You need to add garlic to make it good.

972
00:38:06,917 --> 00:38:07,952
Yes, garlic.

973
00:38:08,019 --> 00:38:09,420
I almost forgot.

974
00:38:09,487 --> 00:38:11,789
The burners are fully occupied.

975
00:38:12,356 --> 00:38:14,892
HE CAN'T SEEM TO GET THE THICKNESS RIGHT

976
00:38:14,959 --> 00:38:16,360
Or add some starch.

977
00:38:16,427 --> 00:38:18,162
-Starch?
-For viscosity.

978
00:38:18,229 --> 00:38:19,930
You aren't supposed to use starch!

979
00:38:19,997 --> 00:38:21,999
That's just how you make it.

980
00:38:22,066 --> 00:38:24,101
Well, you can add just a little.

981
00:38:24,168 --> 00:38:27,238
-That's how you finish the stir-fry.
-Poong is now berating Ho-young.

982
00:38:27,605 --> 00:38:29,707
SELF-PROCLAIMED SOUTHEAST ASIAN EXPERT

983
00:38:29,774 --> 00:38:30,841
Back in the green room,

984
00:38:30,908 --> 00:38:33,411
all chefs talked to him
to come up with their recipes.

985
00:38:33,711 --> 00:38:35,479
REALLY?

986
00:38:35,546 --> 00:38:38,349
-It's kind of unexpected.
-He only talks big.

987
00:38:38,416 --> 00:38:40,518
Wait, the <i>banh xeo</i>.

988
00:38:40,584 --> 00:38:41,919
You have about six minutes left.

989
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:43,454
I can totes do it.

990
00:38:43,521 --> 00:38:47,091
You have to serve
<i>jeyuk-bokkeum</i> and <i>banh xeo</i> together.

991
00:38:47,158 --> 00:38:49,393
Wait, is that <i>banh xeo?</i>

992
00:38:49,460 --> 00:38:51,862
He's making <i>banh xeo</i> in that… Right.

993
00:38:51,929 --> 00:38:53,764
-That's <i>banh xeo</i>.
-He's making tiny pieces.

994
00:38:53,831 --> 00:38:55,733
He's making mini portions.

995
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,602
They'll come in smaller sizes.

996
00:38:58,869 --> 00:39:01,138
RED PEPPER, CHEONGYANG PEPPER

997
00:39:01,205 --> 00:39:04,775
It's usually a huge circular piece
folded in half.

998
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:07,478
We're starting to smell the food,

999
00:39:07,545 --> 00:39:10,848
and Manager Park just swallowed hard.

1000
00:39:10,915 --> 00:39:12,383
I keep drooling.

1001
00:39:14,051 --> 00:39:15,519
Gosh, five minutes left.

1002
00:39:15,586 --> 00:39:18,222
Sung-ju, can you report from the kitchen?

1003
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:20,925
-Let me go check the situation.
-Five minutes.

1004
00:39:20,991 --> 00:39:24,195
I'm here to report
on the 2026 Rice-dink FAFA World Cup.

1005
00:39:24,261 --> 00:39:25,730
What does it smell like?

1006
00:39:25,796 --> 00:39:29,800
-It's smelling like Da Nang!
-It's like Da Nang!

1007
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:32,303
-It's a great place to visit.
-It is.

1008
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,938
These are <i>banh xeo.</i>

1009
00:39:34,004 --> 00:39:35,940
This side looks a bit… Yes.

1010
00:39:36,173 --> 00:39:37,608
PULLS HIMSELF TOGETHER
AND GRABS THE JEYUK-BOKKEUM

1011
00:39:37,675 --> 00:39:41,345
That stir-fried pork
would go so well with plain rice.

1012
00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:43,881
What's this? It's <i>mi quang</i> broth.

1013
00:39:43,948 --> 00:39:46,283
-Let me try the broth.
-The <i>mi quang</i> broth.

1014
00:39:46,350 --> 00:39:49,286
-Four minutes. <i>Mi quang </i>broth.
-<i>Mi quang</i> broth.

1015
00:39:50,488 --> 00:39:52,823
-Is it delicious or not?
-Is it good?

1016
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:53,891
Is it bad?

1017
00:39:55,092 --> 00:39:56,360
It's just plain bad.

1018
00:39:57,728 --> 00:39:58,863
It's just plain bad.

1019
00:39:58,929 --> 00:40:00,331
A BIG SMILE

1020
00:40:00,564 --> 00:40:02,032
WHY IS HE HAPPY?

1021
00:40:02,099 --> 00:40:03,134
It's just plain bad!

1022
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,301
HEHE HAHA

1023
00:40:04,368 --> 00:40:06,103
It's way too bland!

1024
00:40:06,170 --> 00:40:07,004
It's not done yet.

1025
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:08,873
You have to season this.

1026
00:40:08,939 --> 00:40:10,541
Maybe his salty <i>cha gio</i>
will balance it out.

1027
00:40:10,608 --> 00:40:14,378
-I'm going to season it now.
-He'll season it now.

1028
00:40:14,445 --> 00:40:18,149
He's much more composed now
after having a few wins in a row.

1029
00:40:19,083 --> 00:40:20,484
He's adding <i>doenjang</i>.

1030
00:40:20,551 --> 00:40:22,219
AND SOME TURMERIC BROTH

1031
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:24,722
SON JONG-WON WORKS HARD
ON FINISHING UP BANH XEO

1032
00:40:24,789 --> 00:40:27,124
That's what your <i>banh xeo</i> looks like?

1033
00:40:27,191 --> 00:40:28,526
Is this <i>banh xeo?</i>

1034
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:31,595
-He said he'd give it a Korean touch.
-You're right.

1035
00:40:31,662 --> 00:40:34,064
He's topping it with lots of ingredients.

1036
00:40:34,131 --> 00:40:36,033
-A perilla leaf.
-That's the pork.

1037
00:40:36,100 --> 00:40:39,303
-He said he loves soybean leaves.
-Soybean leaves?

1038
00:40:39,370 --> 00:40:41,005
-It looks good.
-Huh?

1039
00:40:41,071 --> 00:40:43,140
This better taste Korean.

1040
00:40:43,207 --> 00:40:44,975
The stir-fried pork.

1041
00:40:45,042 --> 00:40:46,343
-<i>Jeyuk-bokkeum?</i>
-Jong-won's pork dish.

1042
00:40:46,911 --> 00:40:48,312
Is that <i>banh xeo</i>

1043
00:40:48,379 --> 00:40:50,181
delicious, ey, yo?

1044
00:40:50,748 --> 00:40:52,349
THE FORMER STRIKER'S SHARP TONE!

1045
00:40:52,416 --> 00:40:53,250
How is it, ey, yo?

1046
00:40:53,317 --> 00:40:54,585
It must be salty.

1047
00:40:54,652 --> 00:40:57,021
-How is it?
-What's it like?

1048
00:40:57,087 --> 00:40:59,957
-It's so salty, ey, yo!
-It's salty!

1049
00:41:00,024 --> 00:41:01,058
It has to be.

1050
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,894
-It has to be salty.
-It's too salty!

1051
00:41:03,961 --> 00:41:05,729
-It's too salty!
-It has to be.

1052
00:41:05,796 --> 00:41:07,398
-It has to be?
-There's a reason?

1053
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,432
Gosh.

1054
00:41:08,499 --> 00:41:10,301
Do you like it when your food is salty?

1055
00:41:10,367 --> 00:41:11,702
-I do.
-You do?

1056
00:41:12,436 --> 00:41:14,238
-He likes his food salty!
-Did you get lucky?

1057
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:16,941
-It's too salty.
-It'll be okay with everything else.

1058
00:41:17,007 --> 00:41:20,010
4. TOP BANH XEO CRÊPE
WITH PORK AND SHRIMP FILLINGS

1059
00:41:20,077 --> 00:41:22,480
They aren't going into the same thing.

1060
00:41:22,546 --> 00:41:24,548
He's making two different variants.

1061
00:41:24,615 --> 00:41:25,716
SHRIMP FLAVOR, PORK FLAVOR

1062
00:41:25,783 --> 00:41:27,318
Cabbage.

1063
00:41:27,384 --> 00:41:29,453
Will he wrap it with cabbage?

1064
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,622
-It's the Korean touch.
-Oh, a Korean touch?

1065
00:41:31,689 --> 00:41:32,690
That's hot.

1066
00:41:32,756 --> 00:41:36,627
The winning streak will continue
for one of you, but not the other.

1067
00:41:36,694 --> 00:41:38,162
Two minutes left!

1068
00:41:38,229 --> 00:41:39,763
Oh, no. Two minutes.

1069
00:41:40,130 --> 00:41:41,565
CHOP LETTUCE

1070
00:41:42,933 --> 00:41:45,536
AND TOP THE NOODLES

1071
00:41:45,769 --> 00:41:46,904
STARTING THE PRESENTATION

1072
00:41:47,338 --> 00:41:50,875
5. TOP THE NOODLES
WITH PREPPED INGREDIENTS

1073
00:41:50,941 --> 00:41:53,210
SAEU-JEOT FRITTER, GREEN ONION,
CHEONGYANG PEPPER, LETTUCE, LIME

1074
00:41:53,277 --> 00:41:55,012
AND LAST BUT NOT LEAST

1075
00:41:55,479 --> 00:42:00,084
TOPPING THE PORK AND SHRIMP
GRILLED IN THE OVEN

1076
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:01,852
And this.

1077
00:42:01,919 --> 00:42:03,320
What's this again?

1078
00:42:03,387 --> 00:42:05,089
-The <i>cha gio </i>sauce.
-The <i>cha gio</i> sauce.

1079
00:42:05,155 --> 00:42:07,725
-The <i>cha gio</i> sauce.
-Let me try this.

1080
00:42:08,292 --> 00:42:10,127
-Is it salty or not?
-The <i>cha gio</i> sauce.

1081
00:42:10,194 --> 00:42:11,328
It's overly salty, right?

1082
00:42:11,395 --> 00:42:12,763
Is it delicious?

1083
00:42:12,830 --> 00:42:14,431
We're in Hanoi!

1084
00:42:14,765 --> 00:42:16,333
A SMILE

1085
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:18,135
-You're in Hanoi?
-Is it good already?

1086
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:19,937
You know how to make Vietnamese food.

1087
00:42:20,004 --> 00:42:22,172
-Of course.
-Just make sure the <i>cha gio</i> is good.

1088
00:42:22,439 --> 00:42:23,641
RIP?

1089
00:42:23,707 --> 00:42:25,109
Hey, wait!

1090
00:42:25,175 --> 00:42:27,478
-I just saw it! It broke open!
-It broke open?

1091
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:29,547
-That just broke open!
-It did?

1092
00:42:29,613 --> 00:42:31,482
-Where?
-Everything he fried broke open!

1093
00:42:31,549 --> 00:42:33,150
I saw it break open!

1094
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:34,952
I saw it clearly with my own two eyes!

1095
00:42:35,019 --> 00:42:37,488
-I saw it clearly! It broke open!
-There's no time!

1096
00:42:37,555 --> 00:42:38,989
Sung-jun checks the time.

1097
00:42:39,056 --> 00:42:40,491
A minute and 24 seconds.

1098
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:42,960
FOR NOW, POUR BROTH OVER THE NOODLES

1099
00:42:43,027 --> 00:42:46,130
Stay calm.

1100
00:42:46,196 --> 00:42:47,731
The side of his <i>cha gio</i> broke open.

1101
00:42:48,966 --> 00:42:51,502
-Yes, I'm seeing the hole.
-It broke open!

1102
00:42:51,569 --> 00:42:54,471
What now?
He'll have to stick them back together.

1103
00:42:54,772 --> 00:42:57,875
ADDING SESAME OIL
ON TOP OF THE MORNING GLORY STIR-FRY

1104
00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:00,144
He has coconut milk too.

1105
00:43:00,210 --> 00:43:02,713
-Where's the coconut water?
-Over here.

1106
00:43:02,947 --> 00:43:04,181
POONG'S COCONUT WATER, SOJU

1107
00:43:05,449 --> 00:43:06,917
ADD HONEY

1108
00:43:07,351 --> 00:43:08,886
GRABBING ICE

1109
00:43:08,953 --> 00:43:11,555
-Almost done.
-Whoa, 45 seconds.

1110
00:43:11,622 --> 00:43:13,624
-What now?
-Forty-five seconds.

1111
00:43:14,091 --> 00:43:16,026
BUSY

1112
00:43:16,093 --> 00:43:19,530
Will he finish everything in 40 seconds?

1113
00:43:19,597 --> 00:43:23,000
-He's blending something now.
-I'm done.

1114
00:43:23,067 --> 00:43:25,469
-Thirty seconds!
-Oh, no.

1115
00:43:25,536 --> 00:43:28,539
The sauce was fantastic,
but I think the <i>cha gio</i> is ruined.

1116
00:43:28,606 --> 00:43:30,307
-It's not ruined.
-It's not?

1117
00:43:30,374 --> 00:43:32,443
Are you done?

1118
00:43:32,509 --> 00:43:33,844
-Are you done?
-<i>Cha gio.</i>

1119
00:43:33,911 --> 00:43:36,413
-I think I'm done.
-He's done. Sung-jun's done.

1120
00:43:37,247 --> 00:43:39,850
JONG-WON POURS THE TTEOKGUK

1121
00:43:39,917 --> 00:43:40,951
Eleven seconds left.

1122
00:43:41,018 --> 00:43:42,319
Be careful.

1123
00:43:42,386 --> 00:43:45,456
Things are very chaotic here.
Jong-won feels rushed.

1124
00:43:45,522 --> 00:43:46,657
-Ten.
-Ten.

1125
00:43:46,724 --> 00:43:47,691
-Nine.
-Nine.

1126
00:43:47,758 --> 00:43:48,859
-Eight.
-Eight.

1127
00:43:48,926 --> 00:43:50,327
A THRILLING COOK-OFF!

1128
00:43:50,394 --> 00:43:51,629
-Ten.
-Let's go.

1129
00:43:51,929 --> 00:43:54,098
POURING THE COCKTAIL
INTO THE COCONUT SHELL

1130
00:43:54,331 --> 00:43:56,200
THEY CAN ONLY CHUCKLE AT THE URGENCY

1131
00:43:56,266 --> 00:43:58,035
-Four. Three.
-Four. Three.

1132
00:43:58,102 --> 00:43:59,303
-You got this.
-Two.

1133
00:43:59,370 --> 00:44:00,504
-One.
-One.

1134
00:44:00,571 --> 00:44:03,273
He's done too. Jong-won is finished.

1135
00:44:03,340 --> 00:44:04,408
SON JONG-WON'S BUZZER BEATER

1136
00:44:04,475 --> 00:44:06,377
-That was no joke.
-Great work.

1137
00:44:06,443 --> 00:44:09,613
All dishes are prepared just for Hang-seo.

1138
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:12,983
EYES ON THE BALL

1139
00:44:13,651 --> 00:44:15,152
I'm getting nervous.

1140
00:44:15,219 --> 00:44:16,253
You'll have to decide.

1141
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:17,521
And review the food.

1142
00:44:17,588 --> 00:44:19,923
Manager Choi came prepared.

1143
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:23,327
I became too prepared,
so I'm starting to get confused.

1144
00:44:23,394 --> 00:44:25,729
-Is it hard to choose one?
-Yes.

1145
00:44:25,796 --> 00:44:30,634
All Vietnamese dishes
were prepared just for Manager Park.

1146
00:44:30,701 --> 00:44:33,303
Don't these look great?

1147
00:44:33,370 --> 00:44:34,571
Just seeing them

1148
00:44:34,638 --> 00:44:37,675
-makes me feel like I'm in Vietnam.
-It really does.

1149
00:44:37,741 --> 00:44:40,210
I'd like to thank both chefs.

1150
00:44:40,277 --> 00:44:43,347
I didn't use ChoiPT like someone, so…

1151
00:44:43,414 --> 00:44:46,750
-Come on.
-He didn't use ChoiPT.

1152
00:44:46,817 --> 00:44:49,520
So I may not be as eloquent
with my review.

1153
00:44:49,586 --> 00:44:51,922
-It's okay.
-Please be understanding.

1154
00:44:51,989 --> 00:44:56,060
Please try Chef Sung-jun's dish first.

1155
00:44:56,126 --> 00:44:57,928
Isn't This the Mi Quang You Wanted?

1156
00:44:58,529 --> 00:45:02,700
MI QUANG MADE WITH DOENJANG
FOR THE KOREAN TOUCH

1157
00:45:03,534 --> 00:45:07,571
SERVED WITH MORNING GLORY
AND MUKEUNJI CHA GIO

1158
00:45:09,306 --> 00:45:13,711
CHEF SUNG-JUN'S
ISN'T THIS THE MI QUANG YOU WANTED?

1159
00:45:13,777 --> 00:45:16,513
-Should I eat this first?
-Yes, try the mi quang first.

1160
00:45:16,580 --> 00:45:19,683
-If you like lime, squeeze it on top.
-It already looks so delicious.

1161
00:45:19,750 --> 00:45:21,318
SQUEEZE

1162
00:45:21,952 --> 00:45:23,020
THIS MUCH?
YES

1163
00:45:23,087 --> 00:45:24,321
You can just mix it and eat it.

1164
00:45:24,388 --> 00:45:26,323
I also cooked some pork neck and shrimp.

1165
00:45:27,424 --> 00:45:30,894
The soup didn't taste seasoned
when I tried it.

1166
00:45:30,961 --> 00:45:31,829
UNSURE…

1167
00:45:31,895 --> 00:45:33,497
He tilts his head.

1168
00:45:33,564 --> 00:45:36,266
-That's his bad game face.
-Exactly.

1169
00:45:36,333 --> 00:45:40,237
-It's when the players aren't doing well.
-It's an emergency.

1170
00:45:40,304 --> 00:45:42,406
He just tilted his head. He's unsure.

1171
00:45:44,541 --> 00:45:46,343
NODS QUIETLY

1172
00:45:47,144 --> 00:45:48,746
And a bite of the meat.

1173
00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:50,547
Is it cooked well?

1174
00:45:50,614 --> 00:45:51,615
NODS QUIETLY AGAIN

1175
00:45:52,282 --> 00:45:54,118
A BITE OF THE SHRIMP

1176
00:45:54,718 --> 00:45:55,986
LOOKING SERIOUS

1177
00:45:56,053 --> 00:45:58,822
It's hard to read Manager Park's face.

1178
00:45:58,889 --> 00:46:01,125
I'm sorry,
but you aren't here to dine alone.

1179
00:46:01,191 --> 00:46:04,061
-So please…
-The viewers are all watching too.

1180
00:46:04,128 --> 00:46:07,164
-You should review it after a bite.
-Tell us what you think.

1181
00:46:07,231 --> 00:46:08,065
Try that too.

1182
00:46:08,132 --> 00:46:09,500
Can you just be quiet?

1183
00:46:09,566 --> 00:46:10,400
BACKFIRED

1184
00:46:10,467 --> 00:46:12,136
"Be quiet, Yong-soo."

1185
00:46:12,202 --> 00:46:14,571
-He's very cautious right now.
-He has to be.

1186
00:46:14,638 --> 00:46:17,107
-It's really good.
-It is?

1187
00:46:17,174 --> 00:46:19,376
With all these cameras, I…

1188
00:46:19,443 --> 00:46:22,646
It doesn't taste Vietnamese.

1189
00:46:22,713 --> 00:46:25,616
-It tastes fully Korean.
-It must be Korean.

1190
00:46:25,682 --> 00:46:27,618
It's usually made with pork, though.
Is this beef?

1191
00:46:27,684 --> 00:46:28,986
-It's pork.
-It is?

1192
00:46:29,319 --> 00:46:30,521
YUM

1193
00:46:30,587 --> 00:46:33,557
-It's very tender.
-It must be that tender.

1194
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:35,759
That's how good Sung-jun is.

1195
00:46:35,826 --> 00:46:38,128
He made pork as tender as beef.

1196
00:46:38,195 --> 00:46:40,164
He tries the meat with the noodles.

1197
00:46:40,230 --> 00:46:41,965
Will they go well together?

1198
00:46:42,699 --> 00:46:46,670
There is a bit
of saltiness that's hitting me at the end.

1199
00:46:46,737 --> 00:46:48,939
-I really like that.
-I see.

1200
