Make your decision and press one!

1432
00:56:28,485 --> 00:56:29,652
-I did.
-You did?

1433
00:56:29,719 --> 00:56:31,755
We'll see who the show's striker is.

1434
00:56:31,821 --> 00:56:35,191
Nowon-gu's Inzaghi
or Mississippi's Jung-hwan?

1435
00:56:35,258 --> 00:56:37,827
Who did Manager Park choose?

1436
00:56:37,894 --> 00:56:40,029
Show us the result!

1437
00:56:40,096 --> 00:56:44,000
2026 Rice-dink FAFA World Cup.

1438
00:56:44,067 --> 00:56:46,202
The round between two chefs
with winning streaks.

1439
00:56:46,269 --> 00:56:48,004
Sung-jun with three consecutive wins

1440
00:56:48,071 --> 00:56:49,539
and Jong-won with five.

1441
00:56:49,606 --> 00:56:53,877
Who will be chosen by Manager Park
and get to keep his streak?

1442
00:56:53,943 --> 00:56:55,545
Who will it be?

1443
00:56:55,612 --> 00:56:58,581
Is it Sung-jun or Jong-won?

1444
00:56:58,648 --> 00:57:00,417
Who did Manager Park choose?

1445
00:57:00,483 --> 00:57:03,319
KWON SUNG-JUN WINS

1446
00:57:03,386 --> 00:57:04,788
ISN'T THIS THE MI QUANG YOU WANTED? WINS

1447
00:57:04,854 --> 00:57:05,955
Sung-jun wins!

1448
00:57:07,690 --> 00:57:08,958
<i>Mi quang</i> wins!

1449
00:57:09,025 --> 00:57:10,360
NOWON-GU'S INZAGHI CELEBRATES

1450
00:57:10,427 --> 00:57:12,128
Nowon-gu's Inzaghi wins!

1451
00:57:12,195 --> 00:57:14,697
Sung-jun takes the victory.

1452
00:57:14,764 --> 00:57:19,235
It was perfect for my taste
with these Korean touches he added.

1453
00:57:19,302 --> 00:57:22,172
I rarely get to eat <i>mi quang</i>,

1454
00:57:22,238 --> 00:57:24,707
and it was something I've been craving.

1455
00:57:24,774 --> 00:57:27,544
When I got to eat
something that I rarely get to,

1456
00:57:27,610 --> 00:57:32,682
-it had a bigger impact on the decision.
-What he wanted.

1457
00:57:32,749 --> 00:57:36,286
But yours was delicious too. I'm sorry.

1458
00:57:37,454 --> 00:57:38,988
You know what this means?

1459
00:57:39,055 --> 00:57:42,058
Sung-jun won against Jong-won
for the first time

1460
00:57:42,125 --> 00:57:43,159
and he gets to keep

1461
00:57:43,226 --> 00:57:46,129
his winning streak of four wins
after beating the top contender.

1462
00:57:46,196 --> 00:57:48,131
What's the winning dish called again?

1463
00:57:48,198 --> 00:57:49,299
Isn't This the Mi Quang You Wanted?

1464
00:57:50,133 --> 00:57:51,568
That's it.

1465
00:57:51,634 --> 00:57:53,670
Manager Park, please put a star

1466
00:57:53,736 --> 00:57:56,139
-on Chef Sung-jun!
-He's good.

1467
00:57:56,773 --> 00:57:59,042
Sung-jun takes his fourth win in a row!

1468
00:57:59,108 --> 00:58:01,144
He keeps his winning streak going.

1469
00:58:01,211 --> 00:58:04,614
-He's on a roll. Congratulations!
-Thank you.

1470
00:58:04,681 --> 00:58:06,649
I'm so sorry, Chef Jong-won.

1471
00:58:06,716 --> 00:58:08,284
-Of course.
-Thank you.

1472
00:58:08,351 --> 00:58:12,555
<i>This is the second cook-off</i>
<i>played with Manager Park's ingredients.</i>

1473
00:58:12,622 --> 00:58:15,859
The magical witch
who came to take down the goddess,

1474
00:58:15,925 --> 00:58:17,494
Chef Yi Moon-jung,

1475
00:58:17,560 --> 00:58:19,496
versus the crazy
Goddess of Chinese Cuisine,

1476
00:58:19,562 --> 00:58:21,397
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

1477
00:58:21,464 --> 00:58:25,635
We're about to see a huge game
between two Chinese cuisine chefs.

1478
00:58:25,702 --> 00:58:28,104
-Doesn't it feel different standing there?
-It does.

1479
00:58:28,271 --> 00:58:29,606
NOTICES SOMETHING

1480
00:58:29,672 --> 00:58:30,507
HEHEHEHEHE

1481
00:58:31,241 --> 00:58:32,242
The timing is…

1482
00:58:32,308 --> 00:58:34,944
Chef Eun-yeong seemed fine
while she was seated,

1483
00:58:35,011 --> 00:58:36,279
but now, her eyes

1484
00:58:36,346 --> 00:58:39,315
are slowly gleaming with madness.

1485
00:58:39,382 --> 00:58:40,783
See? Look at her.

1486
00:58:40,850 --> 00:58:42,151
We're starting to see it.

1487
00:58:42,218 --> 00:58:43,786
-Cut it out.
-Stop that.

1488
00:58:43,853 --> 00:58:46,756
It's been a while since we had a cook-off
between Chinese chefs.

1489
00:58:46,823 --> 00:58:49,926
Chef Moon-jung
has been cooking for 25 years,

1490
00:58:49,993 --> 00:58:51,895
and Chef Eun-yeong, 15 years.

1491
00:58:51,961 --> 00:58:53,029
Ten years of difference.

1492
00:58:53,096 --> 00:58:55,198
There's a ten-year gap in their careers.

1493
00:58:55,265 --> 00:58:56,432
It's true

1494
00:58:56,499 --> 00:58:59,636
that I'm quite nervous
to compete against a senior chef

1495
00:58:59,702 --> 00:59:01,137
who has begun a decade before me.

1496
00:59:01,204 --> 00:59:03,406
But I think
this might be difficult for her.

1497
00:59:03,473 --> 00:59:05,341
-Why?
-Because

1498
00:59:05,408 --> 00:59:07,710
cooking in just 15 minutes is not easy

1499
00:59:07,777 --> 00:59:09,913
-if you haven't done it.
-Yes, that's true.

1500
00:59:09,979 --> 00:59:13,216
She's done this for 25 years,
so I'm sure she'll finish her dish.

1501
00:59:13,283 --> 00:59:14,851
Sure, she'll make something.

1502
00:59:14,918 --> 00:59:16,786
-But it's hard…
-"She'll make something."

1503
00:59:16,853 --> 00:59:20,156
…to make something decent in 15 minutes.

1504
00:59:20,223 --> 00:59:23,660
-I'll simply show her.
-That's so cool.

1505
00:59:23,726 --> 00:59:26,529
Chef Moon-jung, you have

1506
00:59:26,596 --> 00:59:28,498
two Chinese kitchen knives on the board.

1507
00:59:28,565 --> 00:59:31,301
-One of them looks unique.
-That's cool.

1508
00:59:31,367 --> 00:59:34,771
When I started my YouTube channel,

1509
00:59:34,837 --> 00:59:38,942
my husband got it for me, saying that
I should use something like this.

1510
00:59:39,008 --> 00:59:40,243
-I see.
-Can you show us?

1511
00:59:40,310 --> 00:59:41,711
It looks cool.

1512
00:59:42,579 --> 00:59:44,480
THIS IS WITCH WITH A WOK'S KNIFE

1513
00:59:44,714 --> 00:59:45,882
WHOA

1514
00:59:45,949 --> 00:59:47,450
-I'll slay today.
-She's in trouble.

1515
00:59:48,551 --> 00:59:50,286
-I see.
-It looks hefty.

1516
00:59:50,353 --> 00:59:52,088
If she's going to slay,

1517
00:59:52,155 --> 00:59:54,691
-I'll at least slice something.
-Slice?

1518
00:59:54,757 --> 00:59:56,893
-She'll slice.
-Like she's possessed.

1519
00:59:56,960 --> 01:00:00,129
I think the show only needs
one authentic Chinese chef, which is me.

1520
01:00:00,196 --> 01:00:01,497
Only one Chinese chef?

1521
01:00:01,564 --> 01:00:02,632
HMM…

1522
01:00:02,699 --> 01:00:05,368
I'll prove that empty vessels
make the most noise.

1523
01:00:06,135 --> 01:00:08,504
THE NOISY EMPTY VESSEL

1524
01:00:08,571 --> 01:00:09,405
OUCH…

1525
01:00:09,672 --> 01:00:10,707
IT'S SO FUN TO WATCH

1526
01:00:10,773 --> 01:00:12,942
Since when did Eun-yeong talk that much?

1527
01:00:13,009 --> 01:00:15,044
She's being too loud.

1528
01:00:15,111 --> 01:00:16,779
Hey, I'm here.

1529
01:00:16,846 --> 01:00:19,882
DISCIPLINED RIGHT AWAY

1530
01:00:19,949 --> 01:00:20,783
All right.

1531
01:00:20,850 --> 01:00:24,988
-Our first-timer chefs get a perk.
-Yes, right.

1532
01:00:25,054 --> 01:00:27,023
You have three different perks
to choose from.

1533
01:00:27,090 --> 01:00:29,859
You can either begin a minute earlier,

1534
01:00:29,926 --> 01:00:33,463
stop the other chef for a minute,

1535
01:00:33,529 --> 01:00:36,966
or another chef
can help you for a minute.

1536
01:00:37,033 --> 01:00:38,534
-That's the UNICHEF.
-Yes.

1537
01:00:38,601 --> 01:00:40,470
Which perk do you want to use?

1538
01:00:41,871 --> 01:00:43,172
NERVOUS

1539
01:00:43,406 --> 01:00:44,707
ALSO NERVOUS

1540
01:00:44,774 --> 01:00:47,043
I will not use any of them.

1541
01:00:47,377 --> 01:00:49,512
AIRHORN

1542
01:00:49,579 --> 01:00:50,713
Wow, she's confident.

1543
01:00:50,780 --> 01:00:54,283
You can't change your mind later
and ask for a perk during the round.

1544
01:00:54,350 --> 01:00:56,486
-All right.
-Don't regret this.

1545
01:00:56,552 --> 01:00:58,054
She's so cool.

1546
01:00:58,888 --> 01:01:00,923
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
MANDARINFISH, NAPA CABBAGE, NOODLES

1547
01:01:00,990 --> 01:01:03,059
PRICKLY ASH POWDER, KOREAN MINT,
DOUBANJIANG, LAO GAN MA, AND MORE

1548
01:01:03,126 --> 01:01:06,229
Eun-yeong, an authentic Chinese chef,
what are you making?

1549
01:01:06,295 --> 01:01:07,964
The dish I prepared today is

1550
01:01:08,531 --> 01:01:11,401
My Mantra
Is Winning With Mandarinfish, Sorry!

1551
01:01:13,670 --> 01:01:16,005
My Mantra
Is Winning With Mandarinfish, Sorry.

1552
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:18,574
It's that pose.

1553
01:01:18,641 --> 01:01:21,110
-She added that.
-It really gets you.

1554
01:01:21,711 --> 01:01:23,613
She says that to a senior chef.

1555
01:01:23,680 --> 01:01:25,381
What's this dish like?

1556
01:01:25,448 --> 01:01:28,217
I feel really bad for Moon-jung today,

1557
01:01:28,284 --> 01:01:31,187
but I can't lose
with what I'm going to make.

1558
01:01:31,254 --> 01:01:33,289
It's Manager Park's favorite dish,
mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>

1559
01:01:33,356 --> 01:01:35,024
-I see.
-Mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>

1560
01:01:35,091 --> 01:01:40,797
Mandarinfish is a type of freshwater fish
famous in his hometown, Sancheong-gun.

1561
01:01:40,863 --> 01:01:43,666
There's a Chinese dish called <i>shui zhu yu</i>,

1562
01:01:43,733 --> 01:01:46,102
made by cooking freshwater fish
in hot oil.

1563
01:01:46,169 --> 01:01:47,704
I'll use that recipe

1564
01:01:47,770 --> 01:01:50,339
and make <i>maeun-tang</i>
with an exquisite combination

1565
01:01:50,406 --> 01:01:51,607
of both Chinese and Korean flavors.

1566
01:01:51,674 --> 01:01:52,809
That sounds good.

1567
01:01:52,875 --> 01:01:56,212
Manager Park loves prickly ash powder,
so I'll use lots of that too.

1568
01:01:56,279 --> 01:01:59,082
She'll use lots of it. Very good.

1569
01:01:59,949 --> 01:02:02,251
CHEF MOON-JUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
CATFISH, PORK NECK, THIN GLASS NOODLES

1570
01:02:02,318 --> 01:02:04,620
KOREAN MINT, PRICKLY ASH POWDER,
KELP, RADISH, PERILLA LEAF, AND MORE

1571
01:02:04,687 --> 01:02:07,390
Up against her is Chef Moon-jung.
What are you making?

1572
01:02:07,457 --> 01:02:10,359
-My dish is called…
-Yes?

1573
01:02:10,426 --> 01:02:12,095
Park Eun-yeong.

1574
01:02:12,595 --> 01:02:13,930
Came to Finish You With Catfish.

1575
01:02:13,996 --> 01:02:15,765
Park Eun-yeong,
Came to Finish You With Catfish.

1576
01:02:15,832 --> 01:02:17,200
A STRONG BLOW

1577
01:02:17,266 --> 01:02:18,601
-Is she using catfish?
-It's catfish.

1578
01:02:18,968 --> 01:02:20,670
SEIZING THE LEAD WITH THE DISH TITLE

1579
01:02:20,737 --> 01:02:24,140
-The catfish of the show.
-That was a strong title.

1580
01:02:24,207 --> 01:02:25,641
-Are you using catfish?
-Yes.

1581
01:02:25,708 --> 01:02:29,779
The key to working with catfish
is getting rid of its earthy smell.

1582
01:02:29,846 --> 01:02:32,849
-It's not easy.
-I'll make you think, "You can do that?"

1583
01:02:32,915 --> 01:02:34,117
What? Really?

1584
01:02:34,183 --> 01:02:37,887
-Really?
-You'll be left with that thought.

1585
01:02:37,954 --> 01:02:40,056
-You'll work your magic.
-That's awesome.

1586
01:02:40,123 --> 01:02:42,225
-There's a Chinese dish called <i>kao yu…</i>
-<i>Kao yu</i>.

1587
01:02:42,291 --> 01:02:43,993
<i>…made by grilling and braising fish.</i>

1588
01:02:44,060 --> 01:02:46,562
I will reinterpret that dish in a way

1589
01:02:46,629 --> 01:02:48,164
only I, Witch With a Wok, can do

1590
01:02:48,231 --> 01:02:49,899
and make a delicious dish

1591
01:02:49,966 --> 01:02:51,768
to capture the heart

1592
01:02:51,834 --> 01:02:53,469
of Manager Park Hang-seo.

1593
01:02:54,036 --> 01:02:56,839
And to Eun-yeong,
the OG authentic Chinese chef,

1594
01:02:56,906 --> 01:03:00,309
-I'll show how scary the catfish can be.
-The OG versus the catfish.

1595
01:03:00,376 --> 01:03:04,514
All right then. Let us begin
the 2026 Freshwater FISH World Cup,

1596
01:03:04,580 --> 01:03:06,115
the Chinese cuisine war.

1597
01:03:06,182 --> 01:03:07,116
It's about to begin.

1598
01:03:07,183 --> 01:03:09,218
The OG authentic Chinese chef,

1599
01:03:09,285 --> 01:03:10,520
the staple of the show,

1600
01:03:10,586 --> 01:03:12,989
the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine,
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

1601
01:03:13,055 --> 01:03:15,758
She's here to slay the show's staple,

1602
01:03:15,825 --> 01:03:17,460
the catfish of the show,

1603
01:03:17,527 --> 01:03:20,763
the Witch With a Wok, Chef Yi Moon-jung.

1604
01:03:20,830 --> 01:03:24,467
Who will rise
as the best Chinese chef of the show?

1605
01:03:24,534 --> 01:03:27,970
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1606
01:03:29,705 --> 01:03:32,642
WITCH WITH A WOK MAKES
HER CHEF & MY FRIDGE DEBUT!

1607
01:03:33,009 --> 01:03:33,843
SIGH…

1608
01:03:33,910 --> 01:03:36,512
-Has Moon-jung adapted to the show yet?
-I wonder.

1609
01:03:36,579 --> 01:03:38,881
It won't be easy to cook
in just 15 minutes.

1610
01:03:38,948 --> 01:03:42,084
She refused all perks
and said she'd only use 15 minutes.

1611
01:03:42,151 --> 01:03:45,588
Will one of them have to leave
depending on the result of this round?

1612
01:03:45,655 --> 01:03:48,057
-That's highly likely to happen.
-Really?

1613
01:03:48,124 --> 01:03:49,425
She forfeited it herself.

1614
01:03:49,492 --> 01:03:52,328
-It took her 30 seconds to light the fire.
-Just to light it?

1615
01:03:52,395 --> 01:03:53,696
Water.

1616
01:03:53,763 --> 01:03:55,731
You could've poured the water beforehand.

1617
01:03:55,798 --> 01:03:57,433
Eun-yeong didn't tell me that.

1618
01:03:57,500 --> 01:03:58,901
-She didn't tell her.
-How could she?

1619
01:03:58,968 --> 01:04:00,536
-It was Eun-yeong.
-She was right there.

1620
01:04:00,603 --> 01:04:03,906
Eun-yeong, you didn't show her
how to turn the stove on?

1621
01:04:03,973 --> 01:04:06,542
Eun-yeong begins to prep the mandarinfish.

1622
01:04:06,609 --> 01:04:07,510
Mandarinfish.

1623
01:04:07,577 --> 01:04:10,580
-She's not joking around today.
-That's slippery.

1624
01:04:10,646 --> 01:04:12,081
It took her a minute to turn the stove on.

1625
01:04:13,282 --> 01:04:15,151
TIME TO SLAY WITH MY KNIFE!

1626
01:04:15,218 --> 01:04:17,520
-Be careful with your hand.
-Green onion.

1627
01:04:18,454 --> 01:04:19,856
WHILE SHE PEELS EACH LAYER

1628
01:04:20,156 --> 01:04:22,258
EUN-YEONG IS DONE
PREPPING THE MANDARINFISH

1629
01:04:23,593 --> 01:04:27,263
-Hey!
-Moon-jung and her Chinese chef's knife!

1630
01:04:27,330 --> 01:04:29,098
-Her chopping skills.
-She's fast.

1631
01:04:29,165 --> 01:04:31,667
-That was so quick.
-She's so fast.

1632
01:04:31,968 --> 01:04:32,802
JULIENNED GREEN ONION

1633
01:04:33,169 --> 01:04:34,337
BEATS ON THE REST

1634
01:04:34,403 --> 01:04:37,039
-Right away. She's so fast.
-That was cool.

1635
01:04:37,106 --> 01:04:38,574
AMAZED

1636
01:04:38,641 --> 01:04:41,010
-Are you making chili oil?
-What's she doing?

1637
01:04:41,077 --> 01:04:42,245
Poong's chili oil?

1638
01:04:42,311 --> 01:04:43,512
She's adding oil now?

1639
01:04:43,579 --> 01:04:46,649
She's adding oil?
She only used a little bit.

1640
01:04:47,083 --> 01:04:48,551
LOOK FORWARD TO HER SECRET BROTH!

1641
01:04:48,618 --> 01:04:50,519
There's a ten-year experience gap.

1642
01:04:50,586 --> 01:04:52,321
A decade is a long time.

1643
01:04:52,388 --> 01:04:53,756
1. MAKE BROTH WITH ANCHOVY AND KELP

1644
01:04:53,823 --> 01:04:55,524
Did she add mandarinfish into the oil?

1645
01:04:55,591 --> 01:04:57,960
Yes, she put mandarinfish in the oil.

1646
01:04:58,027 --> 01:05:00,029
The oil doesn't seem too hot.

1647
01:05:00,096 --> 01:05:02,865
Why are you deep-frying the fish
to make <i>maeun-tang?</i>

1648
01:05:02,932 --> 01:05:06,502
It's hard to make a rich flavor
by just boiling it right now,

1649
01:05:06,569 --> 01:05:07,937
so I'll boil it after frying it.

1650
01:05:08,004 --> 01:05:11,307
It's a method often used not only in China
but in Southeast Asian countries.

1651
01:05:11,374 --> 01:05:14,944
That works great for eliminating
the funky smells of freshwater fish.

1652
01:05:15,011 --> 01:05:17,446
-Poong, you're good.
-That was good trivia.

1653
01:05:18,447 --> 01:05:19,815
NEXT, AN ONION

1654
01:05:19,882 --> 01:05:21,117
Whoa.

1655
01:05:21,183 --> 01:05:23,552
THE INGREDIENTS ARE DESTROYED IN A FLASH!

1656
01:05:24,887 --> 01:05:27,623
1. COOK GREEN ONION, ONION,
AND GARLIC IN OIL

1657
01:05:27,857 --> 01:05:30,993
TAKE HALF OF THE GARLIC
AND PUT IT IN THE COOKING OIL

1658
01:05:32,561 --> 01:05:34,363
Fish sauce.

1659
01:05:34,964 --> 01:05:36,565
Hey, wait. What?

1660
01:05:36,632 --> 01:05:37,566
What's up?

1661
01:05:37,633 --> 01:05:39,335
Moon-jung, can I use some <i>doubanjiang</i>?

1662
01:05:39,402 --> 01:05:40,770
-Sure.
-Thanks. Thank you so much.

1663
01:05:40,836 --> 01:05:41,837
She goes next to her…

1664
01:05:43,673 --> 01:05:45,174
THANK YOU SO MUCH

1665
01:05:45,641 --> 01:05:47,810
LAUGHTER TRIGGER

1666
01:05:48,044 --> 01:05:49,045
WANDERING SPOON

1667
01:05:49,111 --> 01:05:50,413
I forgot what I was doing because of you.

1668
01:05:50,479 --> 01:05:52,381
-What's with her?
-I think

1669
01:05:52,448 --> 01:05:55,117
-she came to bother me.
-She sounded so cheeky too.

1670
01:05:55,351 --> 01:05:57,019
OYSTER SAUCE

1671
01:05:57,086 --> 01:05:59,255
Isn't that too much oyster sauce?

1672
01:05:59,322 --> 01:06:01,691
Manager Park also had a good laugh.

1673
01:06:01,757 --> 01:06:02,658
<i>Doubanjiang.</i>

1674
01:06:02,725 --> 01:06:04,160
<i>Doubanjiang</i>? Ah.

1675
01:06:04,226 --> 01:06:05,962
I HAVEN'T USED IT YET…

1676
01:06:06,028 --> 01:06:07,797
-She took it back.
-Looks salty.

1677
01:06:07,863 --> 01:06:09,432
Why do you need so much?

1678
01:06:09,498 --> 01:06:11,367
-That's too much sauce.
-Is that all right?

1679
01:06:11,434 --> 01:06:12,268
Shh.

1680
01:06:12,335 --> 01:06:13,669
THAT GESTURE!

1681
01:06:13,736 --> 01:06:15,538
-If she says quiet, you be quiet.
-Be quiet.

1682
01:06:15,604 --> 01:06:16,839
Vinegar.

1683
01:06:16,906 --> 01:06:18,207
2. MAKE FISH BRAISING SAUCE

1684
01:06:18,774 --> 01:06:20,176
The time is flying.

1685
01:06:20,242 --> 01:06:23,346
Eun-yeong chops napa cabbage
into large pieces.

1686
01:06:23,713 --> 01:06:24,580
CATFISH IS UP!

1687
01:06:24,647 --> 01:06:26,415
-There's the catfish.
-The catfish.

1688
01:06:26,482 --> 01:06:28,851
-The catfish uses the catfish.
-A torch?

1689
01:06:28,918 --> 01:06:30,119
Moon-jung, let me take the <i>doubanjiang</i>.

1690
01:06:30,186 --> 01:06:31,387
-Thanks.
-Eun-yeong.

1691
01:06:31,454 --> 01:06:33,089
Just take it without asking.

1692
01:06:33,856 --> 01:06:35,958
-"Take it without asking!"
-She's mad.

1693
01:06:36,025 --> 01:06:37,960
"Let me take the <i>doubanjiang</i>."

1694
01:06:38,027 --> 01:06:39,228
"Thanks."

1695
01:06:40,029 --> 01:06:41,497
What are you doing with the torch?

1696
01:06:41,564 --> 01:06:43,699
I'm removing the slimy coating.

1697
01:06:43,766 --> 01:06:44,767
The slime.

1698
01:06:44,834 --> 01:06:47,103
She's using a torch to remove the slime.

1699
01:06:47,169 --> 01:06:50,072
Actually, the mucus on catfish skin
has something called mucin,

1700
01:06:50,139 --> 01:06:52,241
which is actually good for us.

1701
01:06:52,308 --> 01:06:53,976
So I think she's using a torch

1702
01:06:54,043 --> 01:06:56,379
to keep the nutrients
instead of washing it off altogether.

1703
01:06:56,445 --> 01:06:58,180
-Like that?
-She's scraping it off.

1704
01:06:58,247 --> 01:06:59,181
What? She is?

1705
01:06:59,248 --> 01:07:01,450
-She's scraping it off.
-Catfish…

1706
01:07:01,517 --> 01:07:03,219
There are many ways of doing this.

1707
01:07:03,285 --> 01:07:05,654
You can use it. It's actually good for us.

1708
01:07:05,721 --> 01:07:08,691
-We do that with eels.
-We do that with freshwater eels.

1709
01:07:08,758 --> 01:07:11,060
-You have to scrape off the mucus?
-Yes.

1710
01:07:11,127 --> 01:07:12,528
Thank you, Moon-jung.

1711
01:07:12,595 --> 01:07:13,462
NAPA CABBAGE

1712
01:07:13,529 --> 01:07:16,599
I hope the fish doesn't smell earthy.

1713
01:07:16,665 --> 01:07:18,834
3. STIR-FRY NAPA CABBAGE
IN DOUBANJIANG AND LAO GAN MA

1714
01:07:18,901 --> 01:07:20,636
You have 11 minutes left.

1715
01:07:20,703 --> 01:07:23,339
-She's almost done frying the fish.
-Yes.

1716
01:07:23,406 --> 01:07:24,640
Let me know when it's 11 minutes.

1717
01:07:24,707 --> 01:07:27,309
-That's now.
-When there's 11 minutes left.

1718
01:07:27,376 --> 01:07:29,245
-You have 11 minutes left now.
-You have 11 minutes.

1719
01:07:29,311 --> 01:07:31,147
I mean, after 11 minutes have passed.

1720
01:07:31,213 --> 01:07:32,481
Oh, after. Got it.

1721
01:07:33,616 --> 01:07:35,017
-At four minutes left.
-Four minutes left.

1722
01:07:35,084 --> 01:07:38,187
Let's see how she preps the catfish.
You have 11 minutes left.

1723
01:07:38,254 --> 01:07:39,155
Four minutes have gone by.

1724
01:07:39,221 --> 01:07:42,224
-That fish looks great.
-Moon-jung makes cuts.

1725
01:07:42,291 --> 01:07:44,660
She's making cuts on both sides.

1726
01:07:44,727 --> 01:07:46,028
FINISHED MAKING CUTS

1727
01:07:46,595 --> 01:07:48,497
-And she puts it in…
-Shake it!

1728
01:07:48,564 --> 01:07:51,067
-Is that flour inside? It is!
-It's flour.

1729
01:07:51,133 --> 01:07:53,235
<i>It's time for me to work my magic.</i>

1730
01:07:53,302 --> 01:07:54,403
The bag is too small!

1731
01:07:54,470 --> 01:07:57,673
She needs a bigger bag to do it better.
The bag's too small.

1732
01:07:57,740 --> 01:07:59,642
-The bag is too small!
-Is she channeling a spirit?

1733
01:07:59,708 --> 01:08:01,710
-It's too small!
-She's not herself!

1734
01:08:01,777 --> 01:08:03,345
She's about to perform a ritual!

1735
01:08:03,412 --> 01:08:04,580
HER MAGIC EVEN REVIVES DEAD FISH!

1736
01:08:04,647 --> 01:08:05,915
Is that fish still alive?

1737
01:08:08,084 --> 01:08:09,552
What's wrong?

1738
01:08:09,618 --> 01:08:11,387
Yes, excellent job.

1739
01:08:11,454 --> 01:08:13,756
-It was almost like channeling a spirit.
-Great work, Moon-jung!

1740
01:08:13,823 --> 01:08:15,424
I thought the fish was still alive.

1741
01:08:15,491 --> 01:08:16,559
I thought it was a <i>gut</i> ritual.

1742
01:08:16,625 --> 01:08:19,295
She coated the fish with flour
and began to fry it.

1743
01:08:20,429 --> 01:08:21,697
Ten minutes. Five minutes are gone.

1744
01:08:21,764 --> 01:08:23,165
SLICE

1745
01:08:24,967 --> 01:08:25,935
-Whoa.
-Green onion.

1746
01:08:26,001 --> 01:08:27,203
WOW…

1747
01:08:27,269 --> 01:08:29,038
She's so fast.

1748
01:08:30,239 --> 01:08:32,608
-Wow.
-Eun-yeong is crushing garlic!

1749
01:08:32,675 --> 01:08:35,411
Moon-jung has 25 years of experience
up her sleeve.

1750
01:08:35,478 --> 01:08:37,179
-She's using her knife too.
-Garlic.

1751
01:08:37,246 --> 01:08:39,048
Eun-yeong has 15 years of experience.

1752
01:08:39,115 --> 01:08:40,850
-She's mincing the garlic.
-Yes.

1753
01:08:40,916 --> 01:08:43,219
But Eun-yeong had been
on the show for much longer.

1754
01:08:43,285 --> 01:08:44,820
Yes, she's using the broth.

1755
01:08:44,887 --> 01:08:47,923
-The broth for <i>maeun-tang.</i>
-Seafood broth.

1756
01:08:49,425 --> 01:08:50,626
She's slicing the radish.

1757
01:08:51,227 --> 01:08:52,294
-Radish.
-Radish.

1758
01:08:52,361 --> 01:08:53,729
She's julienning it now.

1759
01:08:53,796 --> 01:08:54,830
WHOA…

1760
01:08:54,897 --> 01:08:56,599
-My gosh. Look at her.
-That's her.

1761
01:08:57,333 --> 01:08:59,902
CHOPPING AWAY WITHOUT HESITATION!

1762
01:08:59,969 --> 01:09:01,837
She's on a roll.

1763
01:09:02,471 --> 01:09:04,039
-Look at her knife skills.
-She's good.

1764
01:09:04,106 --> 01:09:05,708
-She really is a witch.
-Yes.

1765
01:09:07,009 --> 01:09:10,079
5. ADD JULIENNED RADISH, KELP, WATER,
AND BRAISING SAUCE TO THE STIR-FRY

1766
01:09:10,145 --> 01:09:12,314
Why does the heat seem so low?

1767
01:09:12,381 --> 01:09:13,516
Is the heat okay?

1768
01:09:13,582 --> 01:09:14,850
-Is it weak?
-It's weak.

1769
01:09:14,917 --> 01:09:17,386
-You can make it hotter.
-There's one more ring you can light.

1770
01:09:17,453 --> 01:09:18,921
The fire?

1771
01:09:18,988 --> 01:09:20,456
Eun-yeong gives a hand.

1772
01:09:20,523 --> 01:09:22,158
-To the max.
-Much better.

1773
01:09:22,224 --> 01:09:23,459
That's the highest.

1774
01:09:23,526 --> 01:09:27,663
-Eun-yeong strains the fish out.
-The mandarinfish.

1775
01:09:27,730 --> 01:09:29,899
And straight into the stew.

1776
01:09:29,965 --> 01:09:32,101
-Mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>
-Mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>

1777
01:09:32,167 --> 01:09:34,803
It's Manager Park's favorite,
mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>

1778
01:09:34,870 --> 01:09:37,773
-She's now adding <i>doenjang</i>.
-<i>Doenjang</i>?

1779
01:09:37,840 --> 01:09:39,041
The meat.

1780
01:09:39,108 --> 01:09:42,244
She's really fast with her hands.

1781
01:09:42,311 --> 01:09:45,414
Meat. Pork neck. Making cuts.

1782
01:09:45,915 --> 01:09:47,149
TWO KNIVES!

1783
01:09:47,216 --> 01:09:49,451
Let's go, Eun-yeong!

1784
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:50,553
SURPRISED!

1785
01:09:51,620 --> 01:09:53,656
SOMETHING DANGEROUS HAS COME!

1786
01:09:53,722 --> 01:09:54,823
Eun-yeong joins her!

1787
01:09:55,157 --> 01:09:57,560
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1788
01:09:58,160 --> 01:09:59,295
GETTING DIZZY

1789
01:09:59,361 --> 01:10:00,329
Let's go!

1790
01:10:00,396 --> 01:10:03,933
Yes, this is it! Eun-yeong joins her!

1791
01:10:03,999 --> 01:10:05,467
IS THIS HOW IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE?

1792
01:10:08,604 --> 01:10:11,840
WHY ARE YOU TAKING IT THIS FAR?

1793
01:10:12,608 --> 01:10:14,276
BECAUSE I'M A WITCH!

1794
01:10:14,577 --> 01:10:16,011
THE PORK NECK GOT POWDERED

1795
01:10:17,680 --> 01:10:18,981
Great job!

1796
01:10:19,048 --> 01:10:20,916
Moon-jung, you're doing great!

1797
01:10:20,983 --> 01:10:22,451
-I'm doing great!
-You're doing great!

1798
01:10:22,518 --> 01:10:24,987
TROUBLE BREATHING

1799
01:10:25,854 --> 01:10:29,925
IS THIS NORMAL
IN THE WORLD OF CHINESE CUISINE?

1800
01:10:29,992 --> 01:10:31,994
Chinese cuisine is rough.

1801
01:10:32,061 --> 01:10:34,897
I began to channel a spirit
as soon as you called my name.

1802
01:10:34,964 --> 01:10:37,266
-You're dead!
-This is awesome.

1803
01:10:37,333 --> 01:10:42,037
-Manager Park is crying.
-He sheds a tear.

1804
01:10:42,104 --> 01:10:46,609
He begins to cry
after seeing the two slay a <i>gut</i> ritual.

1805
01:10:46,675 --> 01:10:48,911
That fish looks delicious.

1806
01:10:48,978 --> 01:10:50,746
The catfish is being fried.

1807
01:10:50,813 --> 01:10:55,451
Both chefs are using the same method,
frying the fish first.

1808
01:10:55,517 --> 01:10:59,054
-I can't get into Chinese cuisine.
-We can't do it anymore.

1809
01:10:59,121 --> 01:11:01,390
-Seven minutes left.
-Seven minutes.

1810
01:11:01,457 --> 01:11:04,426
-She's using noodles.
-Noodles.

1811
01:11:04,493 --> 01:11:06,428
That'll turn the dish
into spicy fish noodles.

1812
01:11:06,495 --> 01:11:08,297
-<i>Eotang-guksu.</i>
-Fish noodles.

1813
01:11:08,364 --> 01:11:09,999
In Gyeongsang-do, especially near Busan,

1814
01:11:10,065 --> 01:11:12,067
many noodle dishes have developed,

1815
01:11:12,134 --> 01:11:13,135
so noodles are a must.

1816
01:11:13,202 --> 01:11:15,037
What about Korean mint and all?

1817
01:11:15,104 --> 01:11:17,039
-I'll add some as the final step.
-Korean mint.

1818
01:11:17,106 --> 01:11:20,075
-You have to use Korean mint.
-I will.

1819
01:11:20,142 --> 01:11:23,379
Moon-jung's chopping skills are fantastic.

1820
01:11:23,445 --> 01:11:26,382
-She chops so energetically.
-She's fast.

1821
01:11:26,448 --> 01:11:30,319
-Eun-yeong chops too!
-She's chopping it again for no reason.

1822
01:11:30,386 --> 01:11:33,455
-She's just making sounds.
-Eun-yeong is not her usual self today.

1823
01:11:33,522 --> 01:11:36,925
She's chopping perilla leaves!

1824
01:11:36,992 --> 01:11:38,627
-That's what I'm talking about!
-Man!

1825
01:11:39,495 --> 01:11:42,197
THIS IS CHINESE CUISINE!

1826
01:11:43,365 --> 01:11:45,401
DONE CHOPPING PERILLA LEAVES
IN 3 SECONDS!

1827
01:11:45,467 --> 01:11:47,369
-That's how you chop.
-This is how you chop!

1828
01:11:47,436 --> 01:11:50,239
-"I've done this ten years more than you!"
-Yes!

1829
01:11:50,306 --> 01:11:51,607
She's grabbing the fish.

1830
01:11:51,674 --> 01:11:53,442
There's the catfish.

1831
01:11:53,509 --> 01:11:55,678
Moon-jung pulls out the fish.

1832
01:11:55,744 --> 01:11:57,446
-Whoa.
-Both sides.

1833
01:11:57,513 --> 01:11:59,948
-The cuts were made nicely.
-Look at its shape.

1834
01:12:00,015 --> 01:12:01,950
The cuts look amazing.

1835
01:12:02,017 --> 01:12:03,786
It's almost scary.

1836
01:12:06,121 --> 01:12:08,824
The catfish looks like
it's been swimming in fire.

1837
01:12:08,891 --> 01:12:10,893
-She's so fast.
-It's like a fire catfish.

1838
01:12:10,959 --> 01:12:13,729
-It's like a legendary monster.
-Five and a half minutes.

1839
01:12:13,796 --> 01:12:15,831
-It looks…
-It's a dish that suits the witch.

1840
01:12:15,898 --> 01:12:18,734
It's like a catfish from a Chinese fable.

1841
01:12:18,801 --> 01:12:20,469
-Like a catfish deity.
-Yes.

1842
01:12:20,536 --> 01:12:24,139
-It looks like a dragon deity.
-Yes, it looks like a dragon too.

1843
01:12:24,206 --> 01:12:25,841
It's about to breath out fire.

1844
01:12:25,908 --> 01:12:29,278
Chef Eun-yeong's <i>maeun-tang</i>
looks like hot lava.

1845
01:12:29,345 --> 01:12:30,412
It's boiling hard.

1846
01:12:30,479 --> 01:12:32,981
-Five minutes, Jung-hwan!
-Five minutes!

1847
01:12:33,048 --> 01:12:36,552
-Jung-hwan!
-Five minutes. Yes, I'm going.

1848
01:12:36,618 --> 01:12:40,289
Will Moon-jung slay?
Or will Eun-yeong slice first?

1849
01:12:40,356 --> 01:12:41,757
-Like that?
-Like that?

1850
01:12:41,824 --> 01:12:43,759
She's adding some broth.

1851
01:12:43,826 --> 01:12:45,994
This catfish looks cool.

1852
01:12:46,061 --> 01:12:47,830
-Doesn't it? Look at the shape.
-Yes.

1853
01:12:47,896 --> 01:12:49,898
It looks strong like a legendary dragon.

1854
01:12:49,965 --> 01:12:51,533
-I see.
-Not bad.

1855
01:12:51,600 --> 01:12:52,968
It definitely looks Chinese.

1856
01:12:53,035 --> 01:12:54,770
Moon-jung, let me use
the prickly ash powder.

1857
01:12:54,837 --> 01:12:55,871
-Thanks.
-Stop talking.

1858
01:12:55,938 --> 01:12:57,272
"Stop talking."

1859
01:12:57,339 --> 01:12:58,807
STRICT SENIOR

1860
01:12:58,874 --> 01:13:00,943
AND HER HAPPY-GO-LUCKY JUNIOR!

1861
01:13:01,009 --> 01:13:03,178
What's with her?

1862
01:13:03,245 --> 01:13:05,647
PUTS THE POWDER IN A SEPARATE BOWL

1863
01:13:06,749 --> 01:13:08,283
-Four minutes left.
-It's okay.

1864
01:13:08,350 --> 01:13:09,518
-Jung-hwan.
-Four minutes.

1865
01:13:09,752 --> 01:13:11,053
THE 4-MINUTE REMAINING REMINDER!

1866
01:13:11,120 --> 01:13:13,856
Let me try this. I do like mandarinfish.

1867
01:13:13,922 --> 01:13:16,058
You do? Try the soup.

1868
01:13:16,125 --> 01:13:18,694
What's the mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang</i> like?

1869
01:13:18,761 --> 01:13:20,195
So, Jung-hwan?

1870
01:13:20,262 --> 01:13:22,231
Will she slice this round in half?

1871
01:13:22,531 --> 01:13:24,166
FOCUSED

1872
01:13:24,233 --> 01:13:26,201
Will she slice this round in half?

1873
01:13:26,268 --> 01:13:29,505
-She's going to!
-She'll slice this round!

1874
01:13:30,639 --> 01:13:32,040
OH, WAIT!

1875
01:13:32,107 --> 01:13:32,941
It must be good.

1876
01:13:33,008 --> 01:13:35,878
-It'll be better after it boils down.
-Seems like it turned out great.

1877
01:13:35,944 --> 01:13:37,312
Three minutes and twenty seconds!

1878
01:13:37,379 --> 01:13:42,317
So far, this stew doesn't smell
anything like fish.

1879
01:13:42,384 --> 01:13:43,786
-Four minutes left.
-Four minutes.

1880
01:13:43,852 --> 01:13:46,188
-Four minutes.
-The rice.

1881
01:13:46,255 --> 01:13:48,157
-What is it?
-Is it warmed up?

1882
01:13:48,724 --> 01:13:50,392
NUOC MAM

1883
01:13:50,459 --> 01:13:52,728
-What? Fish sauce on the rice?
-Sesame oil?

1884
01:13:52,795 --> 01:13:54,196
And sesame oil? What is that?

1885
01:13:54,263 --> 01:13:55,731
EVEN POONG HAS NEVER SEEN THIS

1886
01:13:55,798 --> 01:13:57,633
7. MICROWAVE RICE
WITH NUOC MAM AND SESAME OIL

1887
01:13:57,699 --> 01:13:58,834
Microwave!

1888
01:13:58,901 --> 01:13:59,935
ALREADY KNOWS IT'S HIS JOB…

1889
01:14:00,002 --> 01:14:02,638
-The microwave! A minute and a half.
-Yes, the microwave!

1890
01:14:02,871 --> 01:14:04,173
MOVING QUICKLY

1891
01:14:04,239 --> 01:14:05,674
-A minute and a half.
-Three minutes.

1892
01:14:05,741 --> 01:14:07,242
-Three minutes, twenty seconds.
-She poured

1893
01:14:07,309 --> 01:14:08,977
nuoc mam and sesame oil on the rice.

1894
01:14:09,044 --> 01:14:13,515
-It'll get seasoned like hot pot rice.
-Really?

1895
01:14:13,582 --> 01:14:14,616
Can you do that with instant rice?

1896
01:14:14,683 --> 01:14:16,084
Avocado?

1897
01:14:16,151 --> 01:14:18,420
-Avocado?
-Avocado?

1898
01:14:18,487 --> 01:14:21,323
You're using an avocado?
Will it go on top?

1899
01:14:21,390 --> 01:14:22,291
That's new.

1900
01:14:22,357 --> 01:14:24,560
Do you have any leftovers of this sauce?

1901
01:14:24,626 --> 01:14:27,663
-You can try that.
-Can you try the sauce?

1902
01:14:27,729 --> 01:14:29,398
-Can I try this?
-Yes, but not the fish.

1903
01:14:29,465 --> 01:14:31,533
-Just try the braising sauce.
-Her knife skills.

1904
01:14:32,534 --> 01:14:33,936
She's so good with her knife.

1905
01:14:34,002 --> 01:14:35,671
Is it good enough to slay?

1906
01:14:35,737 --> 01:14:38,874
Soup is very important for Manager Park.

1907
01:14:38,941 --> 01:14:40,609
What's the catfish sauce like?

1908
01:14:40,676 --> 01:14:41,677
Hey!

1909
01:14:41,743 --> 01:14:43,545
Do you think she'll slay?

1910
01:14:43,612 --> 01:14:44,880
She has slayed!

1911
01:14:44,947 --> 01:14:46,248
ANOTHER RITUAL BREAKS OUT

1912
01:14:46,315 --> 01:14:48,350
Moon-jung dances along!

1913
01:14:48,417 --> 01:14:50,118
He likes his food salty,

1914
01:14:50,185 --> 01:14:53,222
so he'll enjoy both this one and that one.

1915
01:14:53,288 --> 01:14:57,025
-She keeps pouring the sauce over it.
-A minute and 30 seconds.

1916
01:14:58,227 --> 01:15:00,429
EUN-YEONG IS DONE COOKING THE NOODLES

1917
01:15:01,530 --> 01:15:05,434
5. WASH NOODLES IN COLD WATER
AND SERVE WITH ICE

1918
01:15:06,468 --> 01:15:08,036
One minute. One minute and twenty seconds.

1919
01:15:08,103 --> 01:15:09,905
-A minute and 20 seconds.
-A minute and 20 seconds.

1920
01:15:09,972 --> 01:15:12,441
-It's seasoned.
-It turned out like hot pot rice.

1921
01:15:12,508 --> 01:15:14,109
She's mixing something with the rice.

1922
01:15:14,176 --> 01:15:15,744
Sesame oil and nuoc mam.

1923
01:15:15,811 --> 01:15:18,547
She poured the sauce on the rice
and simply microwaved it.

1924
01:15:18,614 --> 01:15:21,750
That's new. We didn't know
we could do that with instant rice.

1925
01:15:21,817 --> 01:15:22,718
One minute.

1926
01:15:23,452 --> 01:15:25,287
Fifty seconds left!

1927
01:15:25,354 --> 01:15:26,622
Isn't this boiled down too much?

1928
01:15:27,523 --> 01:15:28,624
A little more.

1929
01:15:28,690 --> 01:15:31,827
6. TOP THE MAEUN-TANG
WITH GREEN ONION AND KOREAN MINT

1930
01:15:32,294 --> 01:15:34,696
MOON-JUNG ADDS THIN GLASS NOODLES

1931
01:15:34,997 --> 01:15:36,532
8. ADD SOAKED GLASS NOODLES AND BOIL DOWN

1932
01:15:36,798 --> 01:15:37,933
SLAM!

1933
01:15:38,233 --> 01:15:39,067
MORNING GLORY

1934
01:15:39,134 --> 01:15:40,969
Thirty seconds!

1935
01:15:41,670 --> 01:15:44,039
-Time to wrap up!
-Thirty seconds!

1936
01:15:44,106 --> 01:15:46,642
-Finish up.
-Make sure you have some soup.

1937
01:15:47,442 --> 01:15:49,678
-Moon-jung tops the rice with avocado.
-Where does this go?

1938
01:15:49,745 --> 01:15:51,246
-I'll have it.
-Okay.

1939
01:15:51,313 --> 01:15:53,916
This is Moon-jung's first cook-off.

1940
01:15:53,982 --> 01:15:55,384
Did you add Korean mint?

1941
01:15:55,450 --> 01:15:56,552
I got it.

1942
01:15:56,618 --> 01:15:59,021
-Finish up.
-It's almost time!

1943
01:16:00,022 --> 01:16:01,023
KOREAN MINT

1944
01:16:01,189 --> 01:16:02,524
CRUSHED PEANUTS

1945
01:16:03,592 --> 01:16:04,426
SESAME SEEDS

1946
01:16:05,294 --> 01:16:06,628
MANDARINFISH MAEUN-TANG

1947
01:16:06,695 --> 01:16:09,197
GOES ON THE GAS BURNER!

1948
01:16:10,632 --> 01:16:12,301
JULIENNED GREEN ONION LEFT IN COLD WATER

1949
01:16:12,534 --> 01:16:14,836
9. TOP THE DISH WITH KOREAN MINT,
PEANUTS, SESAME, GREEN ONION

1950
01:16:15,070 --> 01:16:16,338
PRICKLY ASH POWDER ON THE SIDE

1951
01:16:16,405 --> 01:16:18,040
I'll finish first.

1952
01:16:18,106 --> 01:16:19,841
-Eun-yeong is done.
-She's done.

1953
01:16:19,908 --> 01:16:21,977
-Where's the prickly ash powder?
-Finish up, Moon-jung.

1954
01:16:22,044 --> 01:16:23,545
-It's over there.
-Where?

1955
01:16:23,612 --> 01:16:25,280
THE CHERRY ON TOP

1956
01:16:25,347 --> 01:16:26,615
-Ring the bell if you're done.
-Ring it.

1957
01:16:26,682 --> 01:16:28,050
Moon-jung finishes too.

1958
01:16:28,617 --> 01:16:29,785
WITCH WITH A WOK FINISHES UP

1959
01:16:30,986 --> 01:16:33,789
SAFELY TURNS IN HER DEBUT DISH

1960
01:16:33,855 --> 01:16:35,591
-They slayed.
-What's Eun-yeong doing?

1961
01:16:35,657 --> 01:16:37,626
You have to do a <i>gut</i> ritual
to make Chinese food?

1962
01:16:37,693 --> 01:16:40,796
Wow. These Goddesses of Chinese Cuisine

1963
01:16:40,862 --> 01:16:42,464
-live so passionately.
-Seriously.

1964
01:16:42,531 --> 01:16:44,399
Both dishes are finished.

1965
01:16:44,466 --> 01:16:46,034
It's approaching us.

1966
01:16:47,135 --> 01:16:51,239
Everything was made
just for you, Manager Park Hang-seo.

1967
01:16:51,306 --> 01:16:53,742
And now, both dishes were finished

1968
01:16:53,809 --> 01:16:56,678
for Manager Park's FISH World Cup.

1969
01:16:56,745 --> 01:16:59,681
You seemed to enjoy the cook-off,
but you look quite worried now.

1970
01:16:59,748 --> 01:17:01,717
Is something bothering you?

1971
01:17:01,783 --> 01:17:05,854
After seeing their passion for cooking,

1972
01:17:05,921 --> 01:17:08,790
I became even more nervous
about having to pick one of the two

1973
01:17:08,857 --> 01:17:10,859
even before trying their food.

1974
01:17:10,926 --> 01:17:14,529
Also, I hope the fervor they showed

1975
01:17:14,596 --> 01:17:18,300
<i>transfers to the national soccer team.</i>

1976
01:17:18,367 --> 01:17:21,336
-No doubt, the food will taste great.
-Of course.

1977
01:17:21,403 --> 01:17:23,872
Chef Eun-yeong finished first,
so please try

1978
01:17:23,939 --> 01:17:26,108
<i>My Mantra Is</i>
<i>Winning With Mandarinfish, Sorry.</i>

1979
01:17:26,174 --> 01:17:27,476
CHINESE-STYLE MAEUN-TANG WITH MINT

1980
01:17:27,776 --> 01:17:31,880
THE KING OF FRESHWATER FISH,
A WHOLE MANDARINFISH SITS INSIDE!

1981
01:17:32,714 --> 01:17:34,049
PRICKLY ASH POWDER AND NOODLES

1982
01:17:34,116 --> 01:17:37,386
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S MY MANTRA IS
WINNING WITH MANDARINFISH, SORRY

1983
01:17:38,620 --> 01:17:40,989
It'll need high heat. Put it over there.

1984
01:17:41,056 --> 01:17:41,990
Right here?

1985
01:17:42,057 --> 01:17:43,959
-Right here?
-Whoa.

1986
01:17:44,026 --> 01:17:45,994
EXPOSED

1987
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:47,996
-Over there.
-That's the camera.

1988
01:17:48,063 --> 01:17:49,965
It's not your first time on TV!

1989
01:17:50,032 --> 01:17:52,134
-Come on.
-You've been here for too long to do that.

1990
01:17:52,401 --> 01:17:53,802
EVERYONE CRITICIZES HIM

1991
01:17:54,169 --> 01:17:56,238
OH… I'M SORRY

1992
01:17:56,304 --> 01:17:58,273
You still didn't know a camera sits there?

1993
01:17:58,340 --> 01:18:00,542
It's been a while
since anyone stripped it off.

1994
01:18:00,609 --> 01:18:03,178
A TRUE FOOL
WHO ONLY CARES ABOUT COOKING…

1995
01:18:04,046 --> 01:18:05,847
-How should he eat it?
-Right.

1996
01:18:05,914 --> 01:18:08,183
First, mix it well with Korean mint

1997
01:18:08,250 --> 01:18:10,318
and enjoy the soup and the fish.

1998
01:18:10,385 --> 01:18:12,621
After that, add the noodles
and boil it like fish porridge.

1999
01:18:12,688 --> 01:18:14,156
That looks good.

2000
01:18:14,556 --> 01:18:17,059
A BIG PORTION OF MANDARINFISH

2001
01:18:17,125 --> 01:18:19,461
And it'll keep simmering it there.

2002
01:18:19,528 --> 01:18:21,163
Served by the new grandpa.

2003
01:18:21,229 --> 01:18:23,432
It's literally served by a grandpa.

2004
01:18:23,498 --> 01:18:25,300
-It sounds even better.
-Sounds good.

2005
01:18:25,600 --> 01:18:27,169
WITH GRANDPA'S TOUCH

2006
01:18:27,235 --> 01:18:28,070
The soup first.

2007
01:18:28,136 --> 01:18:31,373
I hope it tastes just like the stew
he used to have in Sancheong-gun.

2008
01:18:31,440 --> 01:18:32,641
NODS

2009
01:18:33,775 --> 01:18:35,143
DROPS PRICKLY ASH POWDER

2010
01:18:35,210 --> 01:18:37,779
And he adds prickly ash powder.

2011
01:18:37,846 --> 01:18:40,916
He probably remembers
eating mandarin <i>maeun-tang</i>

2012
01:18:40,982 --> 01:18:43,218
in Sancheong,
a place with clean water and crisp air.

2013
01:18:43,285 --> 01:18:44,252
The soup.

2014
01:18:44,319 --> 01:18:46,088
What's it like? Is it refreshing?

2015
01:18:46,655 --> 01:18:47,689
-It is.
-It's refreshing.

2016
01:18:49,558 --> 01:18:51,326
AN UNPREMEDITATED ATTACK

2017
01:18:51,626 --> 01:18:53,762
OH, THIS IS JUST…

2018
01:18:55,130 --> 01:18:56,665
He's picking up some ingredients.

2019
01:18:56,732 --> 01:18:58,500
-Korean mint.
-Korean mint.

2020
01:18:58,567 --> 01:19:00,168
He takes a bite with some Korean mint.

2021
01:19:00,235 --> 01:19:02,037
INHALES IMMEDIATELY

2022
01:19:02,104 --> 01:19:04,306
It's <i>maeun-tang</i>. It has to be good.

2023
01:19:04,372 --> 01:19:05,907
-Gosh.
-Is it good?

2024
01:19:05,974 --> 01:19:08,376
-Yes, it's just like the old days.
-He loves Korean mint.

2025
01:19:08,443 --> 01:19:09,911
It smells just like that.

2026
01:19:09,978 --> 01:19:12,948
He's reminded of the old days.

2027
01:19:13,782 --> 01:19:15,951
-Try the snakehead mullet too.
-Snakehead mullet?

2028
01:19:16,017 --> 01:19:18,720
-Isn't it mandarinfish?
-I'm sorry. It's mandarinfish.

2029
01:19:18,787 --> 01:19:21,022
-That's his nickname.
-He's sitting next to you.

2030
01:19:21,323 --> 01:19:22,758
THE SNAKEHEAD MULLET OF SANCHEONG

2031
01:19:22,824 --> 01:19:24,659
-He's not eating snakehead mullet.
-I'm sorry.

2032
01:19:24,926 --> 01:19:27,028
SIPPING SOUP IN THAT WHILE

2033
01:19:27,562 --> 01:19:29,297
MOVED

2034
01:19:29,364 --> 01:19:31,166
-It looks good.
-Yes.

2035
01:19:31,233 --> 01:19:34,736
It's on a completely different level
compared to my childhood stew.

2036
01:19:34,803 --> 01:19:36,204
TASTE ON ANOTHER LEVEL

2037
01:19:36,271 --> 01:19:39,808
It's much classier, so to say.

2038
01:19:39,875 --> 01:19:43,411
It tastes much classier
than the stew he remembers from childhood.

2039
01:19:43,478 --> 01:19:44,913
He really loves soup.

2040
01:19:44,980 --> 01:19:47,282
-Mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang</i> is the best.
-Classy.

2041
01:19:47,349 --> 01:19:50,819
She fried the fish in oil
before putting it in the soup,

2042
01:19:50,886 --> 01:19:53,822
<i>-so it'll taste much better.</i>
<i>-Is that why?</i>

2043
01:19:53,889 --> 01:19:55,357
-Yes.
-You're right.

2044
01:19:55,423 --> 01:19:58,760
-It tastes clean and light.
-Clean.

2045
01:19:58,827 --> 01:20:02,097
I made it with <i>doubanjiang</i>,
which is like Chinese gochujang,

2046
01:20:02,164 --> 01:20:04,399
<i>and mixed it with </i>doenjang

2047
01:20:04,466 --> 01:20:07,135
to create that clean flavor.

2048
01:20:07,202 --> 01:20:08,970
-It tastes clean?
-Should I add the noodles here?

2049
01:20:09,037 --> 01:20:12,340
You can boil it in the pot.

2050
01:20:12,407 --> 01:20:13,842
Dunk the noodles into the pot.

2051
01:20:13,909 --> 01:20:15,243
IN GOES THE NOODLES

2052
01:20:15,310 --> 01:20:16,912
And it'll make it thick.

2053
01:20:16,978 --> 01:20:19,047
THE GRANDPA ADDS HIS TOUCH AGAIN

2054
01:20:19,114 --> 01:20:20,615
Look at him untangling the noodles.

2055
01:20:20,682 --> 01:20:22,417
WATCH ME

2056
01:20:22,484 --> 01:20:24,719
THE TECHNIQUE THAT COMES WITH AGE

2057
01:20:25,620 --> 01:20:28,557
-He's the snakehead mullet among chefs.
-He is.

2058
01:20:29,124 --> 01:20:30,458
He tries the noodles now.

2059
01:20:30,525 --> 01:20:33,094
I tried it before she added Korean mint.

2060
01:20:33,829 --> 01:20:34,663
GASP!

2061
01:20:34,729 --> 01:20:35,831
CHOPSTICKS GO STRAIGHT BACK

2062
01:20:35,897 --> 01:20:37,666
Do you need a bottle of soju?

2063
01:20:37,899 --> 01:20:39,000
TEMPTED

2064
01:20:39,067 --> 01:20:40,101
GOSH!

2065
01:20:40,368 --> 01:20:41,870
ANXIOUS, RELIEVED

2066
01:20:42,237 --> 01:20:43,772
CAN TELL THAT IT'S GOOD JUST BT THE VISUAL

2067
01:20:43,839 --> 01:20:46,842
<i>Maeun-tang</i> with noodles is always a win.

2068
01:20:46,908 --> 01:20:50,412
-He can't eat this in Vietnam.
-He can't find it there.

2069
01:20:50,478 --> 01:20:53,081
My hometown is famous
for <i>eotang-guksu</i>, spicy fish noodles.

2070
01:20:53,148 --> 01:20:56,218
But those taste different
from <i>maeun-tang</i> with noodles.

2071
01:20:56,284 --> 01:20:59,721
That noodle dish tastes quite fishy,
but not this.

2072
01:20:59,788 --> 01:21:01,656
It has no fishy smell.

2073
01:21:01,723 --> 01:21:03,458
-She got rid of it.
-Yes.

2074
01:21:03,525 --> 01:21:05,594
What about the spiciness? Is it spicy?

2075
01:21:05,660 --> 01:21:07,762
-What?
-Is it spicy?

2076
01:21:08,263 --> 01:21:11,433
ONLY EDGY AGAINST JUNG-HWAN

2077
01:21:11,499 --> 01:21:12,400
How is it seasoned?

2078
01:21:12,467 --> 01:21:15,537
If it was spicy, he would've said so.

2079
01:21:15,604 --> 01:21:16,872
Give him time.

2080
01:21:16,938 --> 01:21:20,141
-He would say so.
-Yes. What's the rush?

2081
01:21:20,208 --> 01:21:22,143
Dang it. World Cup or whatever…

2082
01:21:22,377 --> 01:21:23,778
THE JUNIOR LIFE ISN'T EASY

2083
01:21:23,845 --> 01:21:26,681
-It's seasoned perfectly.
-It's perfect.

2084
01:21:26,748 --> 01:21:28,350
The soup tastes so refreshing.

2085
01:21:28,416 --> 01:21:30,952
It's game over.

2086
01:21:31,019 --> 01:21:33,688
The OG member of the show, Park Eun-yeong.

2087
01:21:33,755 --> 01:21:36,458
The catfish dish is slowly getting cold.

2088
01:21:36,524 --> 01:21:37,759
THE CATFISH DISH IS TURNING COLD

2089
01:21:37,826 --> 01:21:39,594
-That's it for now.
-Okay.

2090
01:21:39,661 --> 01:21:43,031
Please try Chef Moon-jung's catfish dish.

2091
01:21:43,098 --> 01:21:44,699
AVOCADO RICE AND BRAISED CATFISH

2092
01:21:44,766 --> 01:21:46,868
THAT'LL BRING DISCIPLINE
TO THE WORLD OF CHINESE CUISINE

2093
01:21:47,302 --> 01:21:51,339
SHE'S HERE TO FINISH HER OPPONENT!

2094
01:21:51,606 --> 01:21:55,944
CHEF YI MOON-JUNG'S PARK EUN-YEONG,
CAME TO FINISH YOU WITH CATFISH

2095
01:21:56,011 --> 01:21:57,913
Park Eun-yeong,
Came to Finish You With Catfish.

2096
01:21:57,979 --> 01:22:00,482
-May I serve it myself?
-Yes, feel free to come over.

2097
01:22:00,548 --> 01:22:02,183
You must feel anxious.

2098
01:22:02,250 --> 01:22:04,219
-Eun-yeong's dish was received well.
-I became nervous.

2099
01:22:04,286 --> 01:22:05,854
I should've finished first.

2100
01:22:07,722 --> 01:22:11,293
I tried to reinterpret
<i>mi quang</i> in my style.

2101
01:22:11,359 --> 01:22:12,861
SHARING HER THOUGHTS BEHIND HER DISH

2102
01:22:12,928 --> 01:22:14,829
-So I eat the catfish with the veggies?
-Yes.

2103
01:22:14,896 --> 01:22:18,033
-Like this. With the veggies.
-Okay.

2104
01:22:18,099 --> 01:22:20,168
-Are you going to feed him?
-Are you trying to?

2105
01:22:20,235 --> 01:22:22,470
She's trying to feed him.
Good one. You're doing well.

2106
01:22:22,771 --> 01:22:24,739
SUPER FOCUSED

2107
01:22:25,006 --> 01:22:27,108
CREATED THE PERFECT BITE

2108
01:22:28,243 --> 01:22:29,377
That looks good. Okay.

2109
01:22:29,444 --> 01:22:30,378
YUM

2110
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:33,581
STARE…

2111
01:22:33,915 --> 01:22:35,417
ISN'T IT GOOD?

2112
01:22:35,684 --> 01:22:37,385
FEELS A BIT OF PRESSURE

2113
01:22:37,452 --> 01:22:38,954
Who stares at people eating like that?

2114
01:22:39,187 --> 01:22:40,555
OVERLY PASSIONATE ROOKIE

2115
01:22:40,622 --> 01:22:41,923
Don't be like that.

2116
01:22:41,990 --> 01:22:43,525
STEPPING BACK

2117
01:22:43,792 --> 01:22:45,126
PROVIDING SERVICE FROM UP CLOSE

2118
01:22:45,193 --> 01:22:47,128
-It's…
-Have you had anything like it?

2119
01:22:47,195 --> 01:22:49,597
This fish was made like…

2120
01:22:49,664 --> 01:22:52,434
I mean, it's not like
the usual braised fish.

2121
01:22:52,500 --> 01:22:54,235
What is this flavor?

2122
01:22:54,669 --> 01:22:55,904
LET ME GIVE YOU ANOTHER BITE

2123
01:22:55,971 --> 01:22:57,772
-I can feed myself. I got it.
-Wait.

2124
01:22:57,839 --> 01:22:59,808
-This time, with rice.
-How do I do it?

2125
01:22:59,874 --> 01:23:01,242
-There's rice.
-She has rice.

2126
01:23:01,309 --> 01:23:03,845
I added nuoc mam
and sesame oil to the rice.

2127
01:23:04,045 --> 01:23:05,480
AMAZED

2128
01:23:05,547 --> 01:23:08,416
You'll need a bit of wasabi.

2129
01:23:08,483 --> 01:23:11,953
I prepared this to give you
a new kind of experience.

2130
01:23:12,020 --> 01:23:13,922
She's like a court lady
who attends the King.

2131
01:23:13,989 --> 01:23:15,690
-I got anxious.
-Quite anxious.

2132
01:23:15,757 --> 01:23:19,227
I can feel how anxious you are.

2133
01:23:19,294 --> 01:23:21,029
He's never had something like this.

2134
01:23:21,096 --> 01:23:23,565
It may seem unfamiliar.

2135
01:23:23,631 --> 01:23:25,266
You can always eat <i>maeun-tang.</i>

2136
01:23:25,333 --> 01:23:27,369
I wanted to make you a new dish.

2137
01:23:27,435 --> 01:23:29,504
Please return to your spot.

2138
01:23:29,571 --> 01:23:30,872
-Allow me to leave.
-Please go.

2139
01:23:31,606 --> 01:23:33,608
-That's so much pressure.
-It is.

2140
01:23:33,675 --> 01:23:36,277
How's he going to eat in peace?

2141
01:23:36,344 --> 01:23:37,412
We get how you feel.

2142
01:23:37,479 --> 01:23:40,949
At first, when I had just the fish,

2143
01:23:41,016 --> 01:23:42,650
I didn't realize it.

2144
01:23:42,717 --> 01:23:44,786
But once I had it with the rice,

2145
01:23:44,853 --> 01:23:47,155
it was absolutely stunning.

2146
01:23:47,222 --> 01:23:50,558
He rarely ever uses the phrase
"absolutely stunning."

2147
01:23:50,892 --> 01:23:52,193
HER SERVICE PAID OFF

2148
01:23:52,260 --> 01:23:54,195
-She was…
-He'll have the rice himself.

2149
01:23:54,262 --> 01:23:57,298
-I guess the avocado goes well with it.
-He must've appreciated

2150
01:23:57,365 --> 01:23:59,868
-that she served him herself.
-This is good.

2151
01:23:59,934 --> 01:24:01,569
The Chinese cuisine catfish.

2152
01:24:01,636 --> 01:24:02,570
All right.

2153
01:24:06,608 --> 01:24:09,310
This is the first time
he's having something like this.

2154
01:24:09,377 --> 01:24:11,379
He keeps exclaiming.

2155
01:24:11,446 --> 01:24:13,214
Let me try just one more bite.

2156
01:24:13,281 --> 01:24:14,749
He keeps going back for more.

2157
01:24:14,816 --> 01:24:16,151
Does it smell fishy?

2158
01:24:16,217 --> 01:24:17,952
-The earthy smell.
-What now?

2159
01:24:18,019 --> 01:24:19,287
Does it have that catfish…

2160
01:24:19,354 --> 01:24:22,057
I'm not trying to start a fight!

2161
01:24:22,123 --> 01:24:23,658
Can you ask instead, Hyun-suk?

2162
01:24:23,725 --> 01:24:25,627
-Is there an earthy smell?
-None.

2163
01:24:25,693 --> 01:24:27,662
I was trying to ask you that.

2164
01:24:30,065 --> 01:24:32,300
He's enjoying it very much with the rice.

2165
01:24:32,367 --> 01:24:34,035
He liked that the other dish had soup,

2166
01:24:34,102 --> 01:24:35,837
-Yes.
-and he likes the rice with this dish.

2167
01:24:37,338 --> 01:24:40,175
I've never had anything like this.

2168
01:24:40,241 --> 01:24:41,709
Does it feel unfamiliar?

2169
01:24:41,776 --> 01:24:43,144
No, not at all.

2170
01:24:43,378 --> 01:24:44,412
A BIG SMILE

2171
01:24:44,479 --> 01:24:47,515
When managers see a tactic
playing out just the way they imagined,

2172
01:24:47,582 --> 01:24:49,250
it feels exhilarating.

2173
01:24:49,317 --> 01:24:51,953
When that happens,
I can forget about everything.

2174
01:24:52,020 --> 01:24:53,321
It felt just like that.

2175
01:24:53,555 --> 01:24:56,057
A DISH THAT MADE HIM FEEL EXHILARATED

2176
01:24:56,124 --> 01:25:00,829
<i>Maeun-tang</i> tasted like what I remembered,
but it was much classier.

2177
01:25:00,895 --> 01:25:05,834
This dish is something
I've never had before in my life.

2178
01:25:05,900 --> 01:25:07,335
They were great.

2179
01:25:07,402 --> 01:25:08,703
Both dishes were very good.

2180
01:25:08,770 --> 01:25:10,905
-Gosh.
-You can keep pondering.

2181
01:25:10,972 --> 01:25:14,008
Please try Chef Eun-yeong's
mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>

2182
01:25:14,075 --> 01:25:15,810
This fish is quite meaty.

2183
01:25:17,812 --> 01:25:19,314
SLURPING THE NOODLES

2184
01:25:19,380 --> 01:25:20,882
-It smells good.
-It's nice.

2185
01:25:20,949 --> 01:25:22,984
-After all, it's a freshwater fish.
-Freshwater.

2186
01:25:23,051 --> 01:25:25,353
So I thought it'd have that fishy smell.

2187
01:25:25,420 --> 01:25:27,489
But not at all.

2188
01:25:27,555 --> 01:25:31,793
In soccer terms, it's like seeing
a substitute who came on near the end

2189
01:25:31,860 --> 01:25:34,229
scoring a winning goal.

2190
01:25:34,295 --> 01:25:36,397
It has a really nice aftertaste.

2191
01:25:37,999 --> 01:25:40,869
Did you just use
another one of your ChoiPT lines?

2192
01:25:40,935 --> 01:25:42,270
Goodness. My mistake.

2193
01:25:42,337 --> 01:25:44,072
YOU'RE REALLY ON-POINT

2194
01:25:44,139 --> 01:25:46,074
He used another one of his prepared lines.

2195
01:25:46,141 --> 01:25:47,909
HE WASTED ANOTHER ONE

2196
01:25:47,976 --> 01:25:49,711
I'm sorry, but what will you do next week?

2197
01:25:49,777 --> 01:25:51,212
I'm in trouble.

2198
01:25:51,279 --> 01:25:52,514
CHOIPT IS OUT OF LINES, EMERGENCY

2199
01:25:52,580 --> 01:25:55,550
After the first bite,
it had strong Chinese-cuisine flavors.

2200
01:25:55,617 --> 01:25:58,286
So it felt like I was strolling
near the Yangtze River.

2201
01:25:58,353 --> 01:25:59,854
-The Yangtze River?
-The Yangtze River?

2202
01:25:59,921 --> 01:26:03,158
I was strolling, but when I
reopened my eyes, I was in Sancheong.

2203
01:26:03,224 --> 01:26:05,226
I think the Korean mint played that role.

2204
01:26:05,293 --> 01:26:08,563
You've recently been
making use of many locations.

2205
01:26:08,630 --> 01:26:11,466
Next, Chef Moon-jung's dish.

2206
01:26:15,236 --> 01:26:16,905
This combination works well.

2207
01:26:17,172 --> 01:26:19,374
MUNCH

2208
01:26:19,440 --> 01:26:23,511
The wasabi and avocado
are an unlikely yet nice mix.

2209
01:26:23,578 --> 01:26:27,549
They both used freshwater fish,

2210
01:26:27,615 --> 01:26:30,185
and this one
also doesn't have any funky smell.

2211
01:26:30,251 --> 01:26:32,787
<i>Korean mint and prickly ash powder</i>
<i>play a good role.</i>

2212
01:26:32,854 --> 01:26:35,256
I think you really did slay today.

2213
01:26:37,058 --> 01:26:40,361
When we boil down braised cutlassfish,

2214
01:26:40,428 --> 01:26:45,233
it leaves you with the thick sauce
at the bottom, and it was like that.

2215
01:26:45,300 --> 01:26:47,235
I really liked that strong taste.

2216
01:26:47,302 --> 01:26:48,736
It was delicious.

2217
01:26:48,803 --> 01:26:50,471
It's time to decide.

2218
01:26:50,538 --> 01:26:53,208
-Can I have more time?
-Do you need some more time?

2219
01:26:53,274 --> 01:26:54,609
-All right.
-It must be hard.

2220
01:26:54,676 --> 01:26:57,812
I thought mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang</i>
would be an easy winner.

2221
01:26:57,879 --> 01:26:59,214
But this wasn't an easy fight.

2222
01:26:59,280 --> 01:27:01,382
It's hard. Depends on what you like.

2223
01:27:01,449 --> 01:27:04,085
I think this dish
can really finish Eun-yeong.

2224
01:27:04,152 --> 01:27:06,821
It's like this. We chose this striker,

2225
01:27:06,888 --> 01:27:08,189
but we couldn't get him.

2226
01:27:08,256 --> 01:27:09,657
Turns out, he joined another team.

2227
01:27:09,724 --> 01:27:11,359
No, it's like this.

2228
01:27:11,426 --> 01:27:12,927
I picked Yong-soo,

2229
01:27:12,994 --> 01:27:15,129
but suddenly you show up.

2230
01:27:15,630 --> 01:27:17,599
MANAGER PARK…

2231
01:27:17,865 --> 01:27:19,767
SO EASY TO UNDERSTAND

2232
01:27:19,834 --> 01:27:22,437
You were all set
and about to go with Yong-soo.

2233
01:27:22,503 --> 01:27:24,772
But look! Ahn Jung-hwan showed up.

2234
01:27:24,839 --> 01:27:27,275
-That'd get you thinking.
-You'd be mulling it over.

2235
01:27:27,342 --> 01:27:28,409
Are ties allowed?

2236
01:27:28,476 --> 01:27:30,011
There are no ties.

2237
01:27:30,078 --> 01:27:31,045
Manager Park!

2238
01:27:31,112 --> 01:27:32,914
MANAGER PARK, STOP CONTEMPLATING

2239
01:27:32,981 --> 01:27:35,083
-He just looked.
-Do not look.

2240
01:27:35,149 --> 01:27:36,451
-Look at her.
-She's at it again.

2241
01:27:36,517 --> 01:27:37,952
MAEUN-TANG♥

2242
01:27:39,887 --> 01:27:42,056
The world of Chinese cuisine
will fluctuate

2243
01:27:42,123 --> 01:27:44,225
by the decision you make, Manager Park.

2244
01:27:44,292 --> 01:27:46,561
It's always so hard
when it's a Chinese cuisine round.

2245
01:27:46,628 --> 01:27:47,862
<i>Press one for Yi Moon-jung,</i>

2246
01:27:48,796 --> 01:27:50,231
<i>or two for Park Eun-yeong.</i>

2247
01:27:51,432 --> 01:27:56,204
No one can protest against this
because he's the fridge owner.

2248
01:27:56,271 --> 01:27:57,438
Please press a button.

2249
01:27:57,505 --> 01:27:59,274
-I did.
-He did.

2250
01:27:59,340 --> 01:28:01,943
Who'll be the winner
of the Chinese cook-off?

2251
01:28:02,010 --> 01:28:06,147
Let's find out Manager Park's decision.
Show us!

2252
01:28:06,214 --> 01:28:08,650
2026 Freshwater FISH World Cup.

2253
01:28:08,716 --> 01:28:10,752
Is it the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine,
Eun-yeong?

2254
01:28:10,818 --> 01:28:13,054
Or is it Witch With a Wok, Moon-jung?

2255
01:28:13,121 --> 01:28:15,990
Which one of the two

2256
01:28:16,057 --> 01:28:18,626
did Manager Park Hang-seo choose?

2257
01:28:18,693 --> 01:28:22,997
Who did you pick
as the winner of the Chinese cook-off?

2258
01:28:23,598 --> 01:28:25,366
Who's the winner?

2259
01:28:25,433 --> 01:28:26,734
YI MOON-JUNG WINS

2260
01:28:27,168 --> 01:28:29,470
PARK EUN-YEONG,
CAME TO FINISH YOU WITH CATFISH WINS

2261
01:28:29,537 --> 01:28:31,172
You did great.

2262
01:28:31,239 --> 01:28:32,840
GREAT WORK

2263
01:28:32,974 --> 01:28:34,976
I'M SORRY

2264
01:28:35,043 --> 01:28:36,678
She beat the mandarinfish <i>maeun-tang.</i>

2265
01:28:36,744 --> 01:28:40,014
Was there a change of heart?

2266
01:28:40,081 --> 01:28:43,718
As I mentioned before,
the <i>maeun-tang</i> was so classy and nice,

2267
01:28:43,785 --> 01:28:45,920
exactly like the one I had always craved.

2268
01:28:45,987 --> 01:28:48,589
But when I had the catfish with rice,

2269
01:28:48,656 --> 01:28:52,226
<i>-it kept making me crave it more and more.</i>
<i>-It's addictive.</i>

2270
01:28:52,293 --> 01:28:53,594
Yes, it's addictive.

2271
01:28:53,661 --> 01:28:55,663
My, thank you.

2272
01:28:56,631 --> 01:28:57,632
A HUGE TWIST

2273
01:28:57,699 --> 01:28:59,500
She won from behind.

2274
01:28:59,567 --> 01:29:02,270
-The catfish finished her.
-She did.

2275
01:29:02,337 --> 01:29:05,406
Chef Moon-jung wins a star
on her very first day.

2276
01:29:05,473 --> 01:29:06,808
Manager Park,

2277
01:29:06,874 --> 01:29:08,943
-put a star on her.
-Great work.

2278
01:29:09,010 --> 01:29:12,046
Chef Moon-jung takes her first star!

2279
01:29:12,113 --> 01:29:15,049
Congratulations, Moon-jung!

2280
01:29:16,150 --> 01:29:17,085
That was amazing.

2281
01:29:17,418 --> 01:29:18,286
THANK YOU FOR THE FOOD

2282
01:29:20,388 --> 01:29:22,857
The top scorer of the 1998 World Cup's
last preliminary match.

2283
01:29:22,924 --> 01:29:24,625
A key member
of the miraculous semifinals in 2002.

2284
01:29:24,692 --> 01:29:25,993
He's a legend.

2285
01:29:26,060 --> 01:29:27,228
That's all.

2286
01:29:27,595 --> 01:29:29,664
THE ATTACKS AREN'T DONE YET

2287
01:29:29,731 --> 01:29:32,166
-How have you been lately?
-Recently?

2288
01:29:32,233 --> 01:29:33,935
To better the future of Korean soccer,

2289
01:29:34,001 --> 01:29:35,203
I've been resting quietly.

2290
01:29:36,838 --> 01:29:38,973
Well, I have an entertainment agency
called House.

2291
01:29:39,240 --> 01:29:40,208
HE'S A CEO NOW?

2292
01:29:40,274 --> 01:29:41,809
I do the laundry,

2293
01:29:41,876 --> 01:29:42,944
the cleaning…

2294
01:29:43,010 --> 01:29:44,078
Home management.

2295
01:29:44,145 --> 01:29:45,680
I'm happy every single day.

2296
01:29:45,747 --> 01:29:47,348
-We present his fridge!
-Fridge!

2297
01:29:47,582 --> 01:29:49,050
FULL OF RARE INGREDIENTS

2298
01:29:49,117 --> 01:29:50,451
When I'm low on energy,

2299
01:29:50,518 --> 01:29:51,519
I can't do any chores.

2300
01:29:51,586 --> 01:29:52,720
FULL OF PASSION

2301
01:29:52,787 --> 01:29:54,489
<i>Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off</i>

2302
01:29:54,555 --> 01:29:56,624
<i>for Manager Choi Yong-soo</i>
<i>of House Entertainment!</i>

2303
01:29:56,691 --> 01:29:57,792
-He's using the eel.
-Eel.

2304
01:29:57,859 --> 01:29:59,060
That looks so plump.

2305
01:29:59,627 --> 01:30:01,829
A FULL RESTORATIVE COURSE FOR THE CEO

2306
01:30:02,029 --> 01:30:03,264
VERY PLEASED

2307
01:30:03,498 --> 01:30:05,433
THE REVIEW HE HAD BEEN PREPARING FOR

2308
01:30:05,500 --> 01:30:07,168
The first bite tasted like

2309
01:30:07,235 --> 01:30:09,137
Lee Kang-in's curling shot.

2310
01:30:09,370 --> 01:30:10,338
THE REVIEW EXPERT IS HERE

2311
01:30:10,405 --> 01:30:12,740
It's like Heung-min's powerful shot
that rips the net…

2312
01:30:12,807 --> 01:30:14,409
You already used Heung-min last week.

2313
01:30:14,475 --> 01:30:16,310
-I did?
-Do you only have Heung-min and Kang-in?

2314
01:30:16,377 --> 01:30:17,645
CHOIPT RUNS OUT OF PREPARED LINES

2315
01:30:17,945 --> 01:30:19,414
WHAT ABOUT THE REMAINING REVIEWS?

2316
01:30:22,583 --> 01:30:24,485
Do you have anyone else left?

2317
01:30:24,552 --> 01:30:26,187
-There is one.
-You have one?

2318
01:30:26,254 --> 01:30:27,755
But he doesn't suit this dish.

2319
01:30:38,800 --> 01:30:43,571
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
